transactionDirectionIncoming.description: The transaction is incoming and increases the amount of owned currency

transactionDirectionOutgoing.description: The transaction is outgoing and decreases the amount of owned currency

trendingStickerSets.description: Represents a list of trending sticker sets @total_count Approximate total number of trending sticker sets @sets List of trending sticker sets @is_premium True, if the list contains sticker sets with premium stickers

unconfirmedSession.description: Contains information about an unconfirmed session

device_model.description: Model of the device that was used for the session creation, as provided by the application

location.description: A human-readable description of the location from which the session was created, based on the IP address

log_in_date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the user has logged in

unreadReaction.description: Contains information about an unread reaction to a message

sender_id.description: Identifier of the sender, added the reaction

transfer_star_count.description: Number of Telegram Stars that must be paid to transfer the upgraded gift

upgradedGift.description: Describes an upgraded gift that can be transferred to another owner or transferred to the TON blockchain as an NFT

colors.description: Colors that can be set for user's name, background of empty chat photo, replies to messages and link previews; may be null if none or unknown

host_id.description: Identifier of the user or the chat to which the upgraded gift was assigned from blockchain; may be null if none or unknown

is_premium.description: True, if the original gift could have been bought only by Telegram Premium subscribers

is_theme_available.description: True, if the gift can be used to set a theme in a chat

max_upgraded_count.description: The maximum number of gifts that can be upgraded from the same gift

number.description: Unique number of the upgraded gift among gifts upgraded from the same gift

original_details.description: Information about the originally sent gift; may be null if unknown

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the chat that owns the upgraded gift; may be null if none or unknown

owner_name.description: Name of the owner for the case when owner identifier and address aren't known

publisher_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that published the gift; 0 if none

total_upgraded_count.description: Total number of gifts that were upgraded from the same gift

used_theme_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat for which the gift is used to set a theme; 0 if none or the gift isn't owned by the current user

value_amount.description: Estimated value of the gift; in the smallest units of the currency; 0 if unavailable

value_currency.description: ISO 4217 currency code of the currency in which value of the gift is represented; may be empty if unavailable

value_usd_amount.description: Estimated value of the gift in USD; in USD cents; 0 if unavailable

upgradedGiftAttributeIdBackdrop.description: Identifier of a gift backdrop @backdrop_id Identifier of the backdrop

upgradedGiftAttributeIdModel.description: Identifier of a gift model @sticker_id Identifier of the sticker representing the model

upgradedGiftAttributeIdSymbol.description: Identifier of a gift symbol @sticker_id Identifier of the sticker representing the symbol

upgradedGiftAttributeRarityPerMille.description: The rarity is represented as the numeric frequence of the model

upgradedGiftBackdrop.description: Describes a backdrop of an upgraded gift

upgradedGiftBackdropColors.description: Describes colors of a backdrop of an upgraded gift

edge_color.description: A color on the edges of the backdrop in the RGB format

symbol_color.description: A color to be applied for the symbol in the RGB format

text_color.description: A color for the text on the backdrop in the RGB format

upgradedGiftBackdropCount.description: Describes a backdrop of an upgraded gift @backdrop The backdrop @total_count Total number of gifts with the symbol

upgradedGiftColors.description: Contains information about color scheme for user's name, background of empty chat photo, replies to messages and link previews

dark_theme_accent_color.description: Accent color to use in dark themes in RGB format

dark_theme_colors.description: The list of 1-3 colors in RGB format, describing the accent color, as expected to be shown in dark themes

id.description: Unique identifier of the upgraded gift colors

light_theme_accent_color.description: Accent color to use in light themes in RGB format

light_theme_colors.description: The list of 1-3 colors in RGB format, describing the accent color, as expected to be shown in light themes

model_custom_emoji_id.description: Custom emoji identifier of the model of the upgraded gift

symbol_custom_emoji_id.description: Custom emoji identifier of the symbol of the upgraded gift

upgradedGiftModel.description: Describes a model of an upgraded gift

is_crafted.description: True, if the model can be obtained only through gift crafting

sticker.description: The sticker representing the upgraded gift

upgradedGiftModelCount.description: Describes a model of an upgraded gift with the number of gifts found @model The model @total_count Total number of gifts with the model

upgradedGiftOriginCraft.description: The gift was crafted from other gifts

upgradedGiftOriginOffer.description: The gift was bought through an offer @price Price paid for the gift

upgradedGiftOriginPrepaidUpgrade.description: The sender or receiver of the message has paid for upgraid of the gift, which has been completed

upgradedGiftOriginResale.description: The gift was bought from another user @price Price paid for the gift

upgradedGiftOriginTransfer.description: The gift was transferred from another owner

upgradedGiftOriginUpgrade.description: The gift was obtained by upgrading of a previously received gift

gift_message_id.description: Identifier of the message with the regular gift that was upgraded; may be 0 or an identifier of a deleted message

upgradedGiftOriginalDetails.description: Describes the original details about the gift

receiver_id.description: Identifier of the user or the chat that received the gift

upgradedGiftSymbol.description: Describes a symbol shown on the pattern of an upgraded gift

sticker.description: The sticker representing the symbol

upgradedGiftValueInfo.description: Contains information about value of an upgraded gift

value.description: Estimated value of the gift; in the smallest units of the currency

active_story_state.description: State of active stories of the user; may be null if the user has no active stories

emoji_status.description: Emoji status to be shown instead of the default Telegram Premium badge; may be null

is_contact.description: The user is a contact of the current user

is_support.description: True, if the user is Telegram support account

language_code.description: IETF language tag of the user's language; only available to bots

restricts_new_chats.description: True, if the user may restrict new chats with non-contacts. Use canSendMessageToUser to check whether the current user can message the user or try to create a chat with them

status.description: Current online status of the user

upgraded_gift_colors.description: Color scheme based on an upgraded gift to be used for the user instead of accent_color_id and background_custom_emoji_id; may be null if none

usernames.description: Usernames of the user; may be null

verification_status.description: Information about verification status of the user; may be null if none

userAuctionBid.description: Describes a bid of the current user in an auction

next_bid_star_count.description: The minimum number of Telegram Stars that can be put for the next bid

birthdate.description: Birthdate of the user; may be null if unknown

block_list.description: Block list to which the user is added; may be null if none

bot_verification.description: Information about verification status of the user provided by a bot; may be null if none or unknown

business_info.description: Information about business settings for Telegram Business accounts; may be null if none

first_profile_audio.description: The first audio file added to the user's profile; may be null if none

userPrivacySettingRuleAllowUsers.description: A rule to allow certain specified users to do something @user_ids The user identifiers, total number of users in all rules must not exceed 1000

userPrivacySettingRuleRestrictBots.description: A rule to restrict all bots from doing something

userPrivacySettingRuleRestrictContacts.description: A rule to restrict all contacts of the user from doing something

userPrivacySettingShowBirthdate.description: A privacy setting for managing whether the user's birthdate is visible

is_maximum_level_reached.description: True, if the maximum level is reached

next_level_rating.description: The rating required for the next level; 0 if the maximum level is reached

userStatusLastWeek.description: The user is offline, but was online last week @by_my_privacy_settings Exact user's status is hidden because the current user enabled userPrivacySettingShowStatus privacy setting for the user and has no Telegram Premium

userStatusOnline.description: The user is online @expires Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the user's online status will expire

updateSpeedLimitNotification.description: Download or upload file speed for the user was limited, but it can be restored by subscription to Telegram Premium. The notification can be postponed until a being downloaded or uploaded file is visible to the user.

is_upload.description: True, if upload speed was limited; false, if download speed was limited

updateStakeDiceState.description: The stake dice state has changed @state The new state. The state can be used only if it was received recently enough. Otherwise, a new state must be requested using getStakeDiceState

updateStarRevenueStatus.description: The Telegram Star revenue earned by a user or a chat has changed. If Telegram Star transaction screen of the chat is opened, then getStarTransactions may be called to fetch new transactions

owner_id.description: Identifier of the owner of the Telegram Stars

updateStickerSet.description: A sticker set has changed @sticker_set The sticker set

updateStory.description: A story was changed @story The new information about the story

updateStoryDeleted.description: A story became inaccessible @story_poster_chat_id Identifier of the chat that posted the story @story_id Story identifier

updateStoryListChatCount.description: Number of chats in a story list has changed @story_list The story list @chat_count Approximate total number of chats with active stories in the list

updateStoryPostFailed.description: A story failed to post. If the story posting is canceled, then updateStoryDeleted will be received instead of this update

error.description: The cause of the story posting failure

error_type.description: Type of the error; may be null if unknown

updateStoryPostSucceeded.description: A story has been successfully posted @story The posted story @old_story_id The previous temporary story identifier

updateStoryStealthMode.description: Story stealth mode settings have changed

active_until_date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) until stealth mode is active; 0 if it is disabled

cooldown_until_date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when stealth mode can be enabled again; 0 if there is no active cooldown

updateSuggestedActions.description: The list of suggested to the user actions has changed @added_actions Added suggested actions @removed_actions Removed suggested actions

updateSupergroup.description: Some data of a supergroup or a channel has changed. This update is guaranteed to come before the supergroup identifier is returned to the application @supergroup New data about the supergroup

updateSupergroupFullInfo.description: Some data in supergroupFullInfo has been changed @supergroup_id Identifier of the supergroup or channel @supergroup_full_info New full information about the supergroup

updateTermsOfService.description: New terms of service must be accepted by the user. If the terms of service are declined, then the deleteAccount method must be called with the reason "Decline ToS update" @terms_of_service_id Identifier of the terms of service @terms_of_service The new terms of service

updateTonRevenueStatus.description: The Toncoin revenue earned by the current user has changed. If Toncoin transaction screen of the chat is opened, then getTonTransactions may be called to fetch new transactions

updateTopicMessageCount.description: Number of messages in a topic has changed; for Saved Messages and channel direct messages chat topics only

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in topic of which the number of messages has changed

message_count.description: Approximate number of messages in the topic

topic_id.description: Identifier of the topic

updateTrendingStickerSets.description: The list of trending sticker sets was updated or some of them were viewed @sticker_type Type of the affected stickers @sticker_sets The prefix of the list of trending sticker sets with the newest trending sticker sets

updateTrustedMiniAppBots.description: Lists of bots which Mini Apps must be allowed to read text from clipboard and must be opened without a warning

bot_user_ids.description: List of user identifiers of the bots; the corresponding users may not be sent using updateUser updates and may not be accessible

updateUnconfirmedSession.description: The first unconfirmed session has changed @session The unconfirmed session; may be null if none

updateUnreadChatCount.description: Number of unread chats, i.e. with unread messages or marked as unread, has changed. This update is sent only if the message database is used

chat_list.description: The chat list with changed number of unread messages

marked_as_unread_count.description: Total number of chats marked as unread

marked_as_unread_unmuted_count.description: Total number of unmuted chats marked as unread

total_count.description: Approximate total number of chats in the chat list

unread_unmuted_count.description: Total number of unread unmuted chats

updateUnreadMessageCount.description: Number of unread messages in a chat list has changed. This update is sent only if the message database is used

chat_list.description: The chat list with changed number of unread messages

unread_unmuted_count.description: Total number of unread messages in unmuted chats

updateUser.description: Some data of a user has changed. This update is guaranteed to come before the user identifier is returned to the application @user New data about the user

updateUserFullInfo.description: Some data in userFullInfo has been changed @user_id User identifier @user_full_info New full information about the user

updateUserPrivacySettingRules.description: Some privacy setting rules have been changed @setting The privacy setting @rules New privacy rules

updateUserStatus.description: The user went online or offline @user_id User identifier @status New status of the user

updateVideoPublished.description: An automatically scheduled message with video has been successfully sent after conversion

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat with the message

message_id.description: Identifier of the sent message

updateWebAppMessageSent.description: A message was sent by an opened Web App, so the Web App needs to be closed @web_app_launch_id Identifier of Web App launch

updates.description: Contains a list of updates @updates List of updates

acceptCall.description: Accepts an incoming call @call_id Call identifier @protocol The call protocols supported by the application

acceptTermsOfService.description: Accepts Telegram terms of services @terms_of_service_id Terms of service identifier

activateStoryStealthMode.description: Activates stealth mode for stories, which hides all views of stories from the current user in the last "story_stealth_mode_past_period" seconds

addBotMediaPreview.description: Adds a new media preview to the beginning of the list of media previews of a bot. Returns the added preview after addition is completed server-side. The total number of previews must not exceed getOption("bot_media_preview_count_max") for the given language

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot. The bot must be owned and must have the main Web App

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code for which preview is added. If empty, then the preview will be shown to all users for whose languages there are no dedicated previews.

addChatFolderByInviteLink.description: Adds a chat folder by an invite link @invite_link Invite link for the chat folder @chat_ids Identifiers of the chats added to the chat folder. The chats are automatically joined if they aren't joined yet

addChatMember.description: Adds a new member to a chat; requires can_invite_users member right. Members can't be added to private or secret chats. Returns information about members that weren't added

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

forward_limit.description: The number of earlier messages from the chat to be forwarded to the new member; up to 100. Ignored for supergroups and channels, or if the added user is a bot

user_id.description: Identifier of the user

addChatMembers.description: Adds multiple new members to a chat; requires can_invite_users member right. Currently, this method is only available for supergroups and channels.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

user_ids.description: Identifiers of the users to be added to the chat. The maximum number of added users is 20 for supergroups and 100 for channels

addChatToList.description: Adds a chat to a chat list. A chat can't be simultaneously in Main and Archive chat lists, so it is automatically removed from another one if needed

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

chat_list.description: The chat list. Use getChatListsToAddChat to get suitable chat lists

addChecklistTasks.description: Adds tasks to a checklist in a message

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat with the message

message_id.description: Identifier of the message containing the checklist. Use messageProperties.can_add_tasks to check whether the tasks can be added

addContact.description: Adds a user to the contact list or edits an existing contact by their user identifier

contact.description: The contact to add or edit; phone number may be empty and needs to be specified only if known

share_phone_number.description: Pass true to share the current user's phone number with the new contact. A corresponding rule to userPrivacySettingShowPhoneNumber will be added if needed.

user_id.description: Identifier of the user

addCustomServerLanguagePack.description: Adds a custom server language pack to the list of installed language packs in current localization target. Can be called before authorization @language_pack_id Identifier of a language pack to be added

addFavoriteSticker.description: Adds a new sticker to the list of favorite stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first.

sticker.description: Sticker file to add

addFileToDownloads.description: Adds a file from a message to the list of file downloads. Download progress and completion of the download will be notified through updateFile updates.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the message with the file

file_id.description: Identifier of the file to download

message_id.description: Message identifier

priority.description: Priority of the download (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be downloaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the last one for which downloadFile/addFileToDownloads was called will be downloaded first

addGiftCollectionGifts.description: Adds gifts to the beginning of a previously created collection. If the collection is owned by a channel chat, then requires can_post_messages administrator right in the channel chat. Returns the changed collection

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that owns the collection

received_gift_ids.description: Identifier of the gifts to add to the collection; 1-getOption("gift_collection_size_max") identifiers.

addLocalMessage.description: Adds a local message to a chat. The message is persistent across application restarts only if the message database is used. Returns the added message

chat_id.description: Target chat; channel direct messages chats aren't supported

disable_notification.description: Pass true to disable notification for the message

input_message_content.description: The content of the message to be added

reply_to.description: Information about the message or story to be replied; pass null if none

sender_id.description: Identifier of the sender of the message

addLogMessage.description: Adds a message to TDLib internal log. Can be called synchronously

text.description: Text of a message to log

verbosity_level.description: The minimum verbosity level needed for the message to be logged; 0-1023

addLoginPasskey.description: Adds a passkey allowed to be used for the login by the current user and returns the added passkey. Call getPasskeyParameters to get parameters for creating of the passkey

addMessageReaction.description: Adds a reaction or a tag to a message. Use getMessageAvailableReactions to receive the list of available reactions for the message

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

is_big.description: Pass true if the reaction is added with a big animation

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

reaction_type.description: Type of the reaction to add. Use addPendingPaidMessageReaction instead to add the paid reaction

update_recent_reactions.description: Pass true if the reaction needs to be added to recent reactions; tags are never added to the list of recent reactions

addNetworkStatistics.description: Adds the specified data to data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization @entry The network statistics entry with the data to be added to statistics

addOffer.description: Sends a suggested post based on a previously sent message in a channel direct messages chat. Can be also used to suggest price or time change for an existing suggested post.

chat_id.description: Identifier of the channel direct messages chat

message_id.description: Identifier of the message in the chat which will be sent as suggested post. Use messageProperties.can_add_offer to check whether an offer can be added

options.description: Options to be used to send the message. New information about the suggested post must always be specified

addPendingLiveStoryReaction.description: Adds pending paid reaction in a live story group call. Can't be used in live stories posted by the current user.

star_count.description: Number of Telegram Stars to be used for the reaction. The total number of pending paid reactions must not exceed getOption("paid_group_call_message_star_count_max")

addPendingPaidMessageReaction.description: Adds the paid message reaction to a message. Use getMessageAvailableReactions to check whether the reaction is available for the message

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

star_count.description: Number of Telegram Stars to be used for the reaction. The total number of pending paid reactions must not exceed getOption("paid_reaction_star_count_max")

type.description: Type of the paid reaction; pass null if the user didn't choose reaction type explicitly, for example, the reaction is set from the message bubble

addProfileAudio.description: Adds an audio file to the beginning of the profile audio files of the current user

file_id.description: Identifier of the audio file to be added. The file must have been uploaded to the server

addProxy.description: Adds a proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

enable.description: Pass true to immediately enable the proxy

addQuickReplyShortcutInlineQueryResultMe.description: Adds a message to a quick reply shortcut via inline bot. If shortcut doesn't exist and there are less than getOption("quick_reply_shortcut_count_max") shortcuts, then a new shortcut is created.

hide_via_bot.description: Pass true to hide the bot, via which the message is sent. Can be used only for bots getOption("animation_search_bot_username"), getOption("photo_search_bot_username"), and getOption("venue_search_bot_username")

reply_to_message_id.description: Identifier of a quick reply message in the same shortcut to be replied; pass 0 if none

result_id.description: Identifier of the inline query result

addQuickReplyShortcutMessage.description: Adds a message to a quick reply shortcut. If shortcut doesn't exist and there are less than getOption("quick_reply_shortcut_count_max") shortcuts, then a new shortcut is created.

input_message_content.description: The content of the message to be added; inputMessagePaidMedia, inputMessageForwarded and inputMessageLocation with live_period aren't supported

reply_to_message_id.description: Identifier of a quick reply message in the same shortcut to be replied; pass 0 if none

addQuickReplyShortcutMessageAlbum.description: Adds 2-10 messages grouped together into an album to a quick reply shortcut. Currently, only audio, document, photo and video messages can be grouped into an album.

input_message_contents.description: Contents of messages to be sent. At most 10 messages can be added to an album. All messages must have the same value of show_caption_above_media

reply_to_message_id.description: Identifier of a quick reply message in the same shortcut to be replied; pass 0 if none

addRecentSticker.description: Manually adds a new sticker to the list of recently used stickers. The new sticker is added to the top of the list. If the sticker was already in the list, it is removed from the list first.

is_attached.description: Pass true to add the sticker to the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to add the sticker to the list of recently sent stickers

sticker.description: Sticker file to add

addRecentlyFoundChat.description: Adds a chat to the list of recently found chats. The chat is added to the beginning of the list. If the chat is already in the list, it will be removed from the list first @chat_id Identifier of the chat to add

addSavedAnimation.description: Manually adds a new animation to the list of saved animations. The new animation is added to the beginning of the list. If the animation was already in the list, it is removed first.

animation.description: The animation file to be added. Only animations known to the server (i.e., successfully sent via a message) can be added to the list

addSavedNotificationSound.description: Adds a new notification sound to the list of saved notification sounds. The new notification sound is added to the top of the list. If it is already in the list, its position isn't changed @sound Notification sound file to add

addStickerToSet.description: Adds a new sticker to a set

name.description: Sticker set name. The sticker set must be owned by the current user, and contain less than 200 stickers for custom emoji sticker sets and less than 120 otherwise

sticker.description: Sticker to add to the set

user_id.description: Sticker set owner; ignored for regular users

addStoryAlbumStories.description: Adds stories to the beginning of a previously created story album. If the album is owned by a supergroup or a channel chat, then

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that owns the stories

story_ids.description: Identifier of the stories to add to the album; 1-getOption("story_album_size_max") identifiers.

allowBotToSendMessages.description: Allows the specified bot to send messages to the user @bot_user_id Identifier of the target bot

allowUnpaidMessagesFromUser.description: Allows the specified user to send unpaid private messages to the current user by adding a rule to userPrivacySettingAllowUnpaidMessages

refund_payments.description: Pass true to refund the user previously paid messages

user_id.description: Identifier of the user

answerCallbackQuery.description: Sets the result of a callback query; for bots only

cache_time.description: Time during which the result of the query can be cached, in seconds

show_alert.description: Pass true to show an alert to the user instead of a toast notification

text.description: Text of the answer

url.description: URL to be opened

answerCustomQuery.description: Answers a custom query; for bots only @custom_query_id Identifier of a custom query @data JSON-serialized answer to the query

answerInlineQuery.description: Sets the result of an inline query; for bots only

button.description: Button to be shown above inline query results; pass null if none

cache_time.description: Allowed time to cache the results of the query, in seconds

is_personal.description: Pass true if results may be cached and returned only for the user who sent the query. By default, results may be returned to any user who sends the same query

next_offset.description: Offset for the next inline query; pass an empty string if there are no more results

answerPreCheckoutQuery.description: Sets the result of a pre-checkout query; for bots only @pre_checkout_query_id Identifier of the pre-checkout query @error_message An error message, empty on success

answerShippingQuery.description: Sets the result of a shipping query; for bots only @shipping_query_id Identifier of the shipping query @shipping_options Available shipping options @error_message An error message, empty on success

answerWebAppQuery.description: Sets the result of interaction with a Web App and sends corresponding message on behalf of the user to the chat from which the query originated; for bots only

web_app_query_id.description: Identifier of the Web App query

applyPremiumGiftCode.description: Applies a Telegram Premium gift code @code The code to apply

approveSuggestedPost.description: Approves a suggested post in a channel direct messages chat

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat

message_id.description: Identifier of the message with the suggested post. Use messageProperties.can_be_approved to check whether the suggested post can be approved

send_date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the post is expected to be published; pass 0 if the date has already been chosen. If specified,

assignStoreTransaction.description: Informs server about an in-store purchase. For official applications only @transaction Information about the transaction @purpose Transaction purpose

banChatMember.description: Bans a member in a chat; requires can_restrict_members administrator right. Members can't be banned in private or secret chats. In supergroups and channels, the user will not be able to return to the group on their own using invite links, etc., unless unbanned first

banned_until_date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) when the user will be unbanned; 0 if never. If the user is banned for more than 366 days or for less than 30 seconds from the current time, the user is considered to be banned forever. Ignored in basic groups and if a chat is banned

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

revoke_messages.description: Pass true to delete all messages in the chat for the user who is being removed. Always true for supergroups and channels

banGroupCallParticipants.description: Bans users from a group call not bound to a chat; requires groupCall.is_owned. Only the owner of the group call can invite the banned users back

user_ids.description: Identifiers of group call participants to ban; identifiers of unknown users from the update updateGroupCallParticipants can be also passed to the method

blockMessageSenderFromReplies.description: Blocks an original sender of a message in the Replies chat

delete_all_messages.description: Pass true to delete all messages from the same sender

delete_message.description: Pass true to delete the message

message_id.description: The identifier of an incoming message in the Replies chat

report_spam.description: Pass true to report the sender to the Telegram moderators

boostChat.description: Boosts a chat and returns the list of available chat boost slots for the current user after the boost

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

slot_ids.description: Identifiers of boost slots of the current user from which to apply boosts to the chat

buyGiftUpgrade.description: Pays for upgrade of a regular gift that is owned by another user or channel chat

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that owns the gift

prepaid_upgrade_hash.description: Prepaid upgrade hash as received along with the gift

star_count.description: The Telegram Star amount the user agreed to pay for the upgrade; must be equal to gift.upgrade_star_count

canBotSendMessages.description: Checks whether the specified bot can send messages to the user. Returns a 404 error if can't and the access can be granted by call to allowBotToSendMessages @bot_user_id Identifier of the target bot

canPostStory.description: Checks whether the current user can post a story on behalf of a chat; requires can_post_stories administrator right for supergroup and channel chats

chat_id.description: Chat identifier. Pass Saved Messages chat identifier when posting a story on behalf of the current user

canPurchaseFromStore.description: Checks whether an in-store purchase is possible. Must be called before any in-store purchase. For official applications only @purpose Transaction purpose

canSendGift.description: Checks whether a gift with next_send_date in the future can be sent already

gift_id.description: Identifier of the gift to send

canSendMessageToUser.description: Checks whether the current user can message another user or try to create a chat with them

only_local.description: Pass true to get only locally available information without sending network requests

user_id.description: Identifier of the other user

canTransferOwnership.description: Checks whether the current session can be used to transfer a chat ownership to another user

cancelDownloadFile.description: Stops the downloading of a file. If a file has already been downloaded, does nothing @file_id Identifier of a file to stop downloading @only_if_pending Pass true to stop downloading only if it hasn't been started, i.e. request hasn't been sent to server

cancelPasswordReset.description: Cancels reset of 2-step verification password. The method can be called if passwordState.pending_reset_date > 0

cancelPreliminaryUploadFile.description: Stops the preliminary uploading of a file. Supported only for files uploaded by using preliminaryUploadFile @file_id Identifier of the file to stop uploading

cancelRecoveryEmailAddressVerification.description: Cancels verification of the 2-step verification recovery email address

changeImportedContacts.description: Changes imported contacts using the list of contacts saved on the device. Imports newly added contacts and, if at least the file database is enabled, deletes recently deleted contacts.

contacts.description: The new list of contacts to import

changeStickerSet.description: Installs/uninstalls or activates/archives a sticker set @set_id Identifier of the sticker set @is_installed The new value of is_installed @is_archived The new value of is_archived. A sticker set can't be installed and archived simultaneously

checkAuthenticationBotToken.description: Checks the authentication token of a bot; to log in as a bot. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber. Can be used instead of setAuthenticationPhoneNumber and checkAuthenticationCode to log in @token The bot token

checkAuthenticationCode.description: Checks the authentication code. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode @code Authentication code to check

checkAuthenticationEmailCode.description: Checks the authentication of an email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailCode @code Email address authentication to check

checkAuthenticationPasskey.description: Checks a passkey to log in to the corresponding account. Call getAuthenticationPasskeyParameters to get parameters for the passkey. Works only when the current authorization state is

authenticator_data.description: Authenticator data of the application that created the credential

checkAuthenticationPassword.description: Checks the 2-step verification password for correctness. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword @password The 2-step verification password to check

checkAuthenticationPasswordRecoveryCode.description: Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword @recovery_code Recovery code to check

checkAuthenticationPremiumPurchase.description: Checks whether an in-store purchase of Telegram Premium is possible before authorization. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPremiumPurchase

amount.description: Paid amount, in the smallest units of the currency

currency.description: ISO 4217 currency code of the payment currency

checkChatFolderInviteLink.description: Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat folder and returns information about the corresponding chat folder @invite_link Invite link to be checked

checkChatInviteLink.description: Checks the validity of an invite link for a chat and returns information about the corresponding chat @invite_link Invite link to be checked

checkChatUsername.description: Checks whether a username can be set for a chat @chat_id Chat identifier; must be identifier of a supergroup chat, or a channel chat, or a private chat with self, or 0 if the chat is being created @username Username to be checked

checkCreatedPublicChatsLimit.description: Checks whether the maximum number of owned public chats has been reached. Returns corresponding error if the limit was reached. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium @type Type of the public chats, for which to check the limit

checkEmailAddressVerificationCode.description: Checks the email address verification code for Telegram Passport @code Verification code to check

checkLoginEmailAddressCode.description: Checks the login email address authentication @code Email address authentication to check

checkPasswordRecoveryCode.description: Checks whether a 2-step verification password recovery code sent to an email address is valid @recovery_code Recovery code to check

checkPhoneNumberCode.description: Checks the authentication code and completes the request for which the code was sent if appropriate @code Authentication code to check

checkPremiumGiftCode.description: Returns information about a Telegram Premium gift code @code The code to check

checkQuickReplyShortcutName.description: Checks validness of a name for a quick reply shortcut. Can be called synchronously @name The name of the shortcut; 1-32 characters

checkRecoveryEmailAddressCode.description: Checks the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code @code Verification code to check

checkStickerSetName.description: Checks whether a name can be used for a new sticker set @name Name to be checked

checkWebAppFileDownload.description: Checks whether a file can be downloaded and saved locally by Web App request

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot, providing the Web App

url.description: URL of the file

cleanFileName.description: Removes potentially dangerous characters from the name of a file. Returns an empty string on failure. Can be called synchronously @file_name File name or path to the file

clearAllDraftMessages.description: Clears message drafts in all chats @exclude_secret_chats Pass true to keep local message drafts in secret chats

clearAutosaveSettingsExceptions.description: Clears the list of all autosave settings exceptions. The method is guaranteed to work only after at least one call to getAutosaveSettings

clearImportedContacts.description: Clears all imported contacts, contact list remains unchanged

clearRecentEmojiStatuses.description: Clears the list of recently used emoji statuses for self status

clearRecentReactions.description: Clears the list of recently used reactions

clearRecentStickers.description: Clears the list of recently used stickers @is_attached Pass true to clear the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to clear the list of recently sent stickers

clearRecentlyFoundChats.description: Clears the list of recently found chats

clearSearchedForTags.description: Clears the list of recently searched for hashtags or cashtags @clear_cashtags Pass true to clear the list of recently searched for cashtags; otherwise, the list of recently searched for hashtags will be cleared

clickAnimatedEmojiMessage.description: Informs TDLib that a message with an animated emoji was clicked by the user. Returns a big animated sticker to be played or a 404 error if usual animation needs to be played @chat_id Chat identifier of the message @message_id Identifier of the clicked message

clickChatSponsoredMessage.description: Informs TDLib that the user opened the sponsored chat via the button, the name, the chat photo, a mention in the sponsored message text, or the media in the sponsored message

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the sponsored message

from_fullscreen.description: Pass true if the user expanded the video from the sponsored message fullscreen before the click

is_media_click.description: Pass true if the media was clicked in the sponsored message

message_id.description: Identifier of the sponsored message

clickPremiumSubscriptionButton.description: Informs TDLib that the user clicked Premium subscription button on the Premium features screen

clickVideoMessageAdvertisement.description: Informs TDLib that the user clicked a video message advertisement @advertisement_unique_id Unique identifier of the advertisement

close.description: Closes the TDLib instance. All databases will be flushed to disk and properly closed. After the close completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent. Can be called before initialization

closeChat.description: Informs TDLib that the chat is closed by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed @chat_id Chat identifier

closeGiftAuction.description: Informs TDLib that a gift auction was closed by the user @gift_id Identifier of the gift, which auction was closed

closeSecretChat.description: Closes a secret chat, effectively transferring its state to secretChatStateClosed @secret_chat_id Secret chat identifier

closeStory.description: Informs TDLib that a story is closed by the user

story_poster_chat_id.description: The identifier of the poster of the story to close

closeWebApp.description: Informs TDLib that a previously opened Web App was closed @web_app_launch_id Identifier of Web App launch, received from openWebApp

commitPendingLiveStoryReactions.description: Applies all pending paid reactions in a live story group call @group_call_id Group call identifier

commitPendingPaidMessageReactions.description: Applies all pending paid reactions on a message @chat_id Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs @message_id Identifier of the message

confirmQrCodeAuthentication.description: Confirms QR code authentication on another device. Returns created session on success @link A link from a QR code. The link must be scanned by the in-app camera

confirmSession.description: Confirms an unconfirmed session of the current user from another device @session_id Session identifier

connectAffiliateProgram.description: Connects an affiliate program to the given affiliate. Returns information about the connected affiliate program

affiliate.description: The affiliate to which the affiliate program will be connected

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot, which affiliate program is connected

craftGift.description: Crafts a new gift from other gifts that will be permanently lost

received_gift_ids.description: Identifier of the gifts to use for crafting

createBasicGroupChat.description: Returns an existing chat corresponding to a known basic group @basic_group_id Basic group identifier @force Pass true to create the chat without a network request. In this case all information about the chat except its type, title and photo can be incorrect

message_id.description: Identifier of the message. Use messageProperties.can_edit_scheduling_state to check whether the message is suitable

scheduling_state.description: The new message scheduling state; pass null to send the message immediately. Must be null for messages in the state messageSchedulingStateSendWhenVideoProcessed

editMessageText.description: Edits the text of a message (or a text of a game message). Returns the edited message after the edit is completed on the server side

chat_id.description: The chat the message belongs to

input_message_content.description: New text content of the message. Must be of type inputMessageText

message_id.description: Identifier of the message. Use messageProperties.can_be_edited to check whether the message can be edited

reply_markup.description: The new message reply markup; pass null if none; for bots only

editProxy.description: Edits an existing proxy server for network requests. Can be called before authorization

enable.description: Pass true to immediately enable the proxy

proxy.description: The new information about the proxy

editQuickReplyMessage.description: Asynchronously edits the text, media or caption of a quick reply message. Use quickReplyMessage.can_be_edited to check whether a message can be edited.

input_message_content.description: New content of the message. Must be one of the following types: inputMessageAnimation, inputMessageAudio, inputMessageChecklist, inputMessageDocument, inputMessagePhoto, inputMessageText, or inputMessageVideo

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

shortcut_id.description: Unique identifier of the quick reply shortcut with the message

editStarSubscription.description: Cancels or re-enables Telegram Star subscription

subscription_id.description: Identifier of the subscription to change

editStory.description: Changes content and caption of a story. Can be called only if story.can_be_edited == true

areas.description: New clickable rectangle areas to be shown on the story media; pass null to keep the current areas. Areas can't be edited if story content isn't changed

caption.description: New story caption; pass null to keep the current caption

content.description: New content of the story; pass null to keep the current content

story_id.description: Identifier of the story to edit

story_poster_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that posted the story

editStoryCover.description: Changes cover of a video story. Can be called only if story.can_be_edited == true and the story isn't being edited now

cover_frame_timestamp.description: New timestamp of the frame, which will be used as video thumbnail

story_id.description: Identifier of the story to edit

story_poster_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that posted the story

editUserStarSubscription.description: Cancels or re-enables Telegram Star subscription for a user; for bots only

is_canceled.description: Pass true to cancel the subscription; pass false to allow the user to enable it

telegram_payment_charge_id.description: Telegram payment identifier of the subscription

user_id.description: User identifier

enableProxy.description: Enables a proxy. Only one proxy can be enabled at a time. Can be called before authorization @proxy_id Proxy identifier

encryptGroupCallData.description: Encrypts group call data before sending them over network using tgcalls

data_channel.description: Data channel for which data is encrypted

group_call_id.description: Group call identifier. The call must not be a video chat

unencrypted_prefix_size.description: Size of data prefix that must be kept unencrypted

endGroupCall.description: Ends a group call. Requires groupCall.can_be_managed right for video chats and live stories or groupCall.is_owned otherwise @group_call_id Group call identifier

endGroupCallRecording.description: Ends recording of an active group call; for video chats only. Requires groupCall.can_be_managed right @group_call_id Group call identifier

endGroupCallScreenSharing.description: Ends screen sharing in a joined group call; not supported in live stories @group_call_id Group call identifier

error.description: If passed, the file generation has failed and must be terminated; pass null if the file generation succeeded

generation_id.description: The identifier of the generation process

forwardMessages.description: Forwards previously sent messages. Returns the forwarded messages in the same order as the message identifiers passed in message_ids. If a message can't be forwarded, null will be returned instead of the message

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which to forward messages

from_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat from which to forward messages

message_ids.description: Identifiers of the messages to forward. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order. At most 100 messages can be forwarded simultaneously. A message can be forwarded only if messageProperties.can_be_forwarded

options.description: Options to be used to send the messages; pass null to use default options

remove_caption.description: Pass true to remove media captions of message copies. Ignored if send_copy is false

send_copy.description: Pass true to copy content of the messages without reference to the original sender. Always true if the messages are forwarded to a secret chat or are local.

topic_id.description: Topic in which the messages will be forwarded; message threads aren't supported; pass null if none

getAccountTtl.description: Returns the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted

getActiveSessions.description: Returns all active sessions of the current user

getAllPassportElements.description: Returns all available Telegram Passport elements @password The 2-step verification password of the current user

getAllStickerEmojis.description: Returns unique emoji that correspond to stickers to be found by the getStickers(sticker_type, query, 1000000, chat_id)

chat_id.description: Chat identifier for which to find stickers

return_only_main_emoji.description: Pass true if only main emoji for each found sticker must be included in the result

sticker_type.description: Type of the stickers to search for

getAnimatedEmoji.description: Returns an animated emoji corresponding to a given emoji. Returns a 404 error if the emoji has no animated emoji @emoji The emoji

getApplicationConfig.description: Returns application config, provided by the server. Can be called before authorization

getApplicationDownloadLink.description: Returns the link for downloading official Telegram application to be used when the current user invites friends to Telegram

getArchiveChatListSettings.description: Returns settings for automatic moving of chats to and from the Archive chat lists

getArchivedStickerSets.description: Returns a list of archived sticker sets

limit.description: The maximum number of sticker sets to return; up to 100

offset_sticker_set_id.description: Identifier of the sticker set from which to return the result; use 0 to get results from the beginning

sticker_type.description: Type of the sticker sets to return

getAttachedStickerSets.description: Returns a list of sticker sets attached to a file, including regular, mask, and emoji sticker sets. Currently, only animations, photos, and videos can have attached sticker sets @file_id File identifier

getAttachmentMenuBot.description: Returns information about a bot that can be added to attachment or side menu @bot_user_id Bot's user identifier

getAuthenticationPasskeyParameters.description: Returns parameters for authentication using a passkey as JSON-serialized string

getAuthorizationState.description: Returns the current authorization state. This is an offline method. For informational purposes only. Use updateAuthorizationState instead to maintain the current authorization state. Can be called before initialization

getAutoDownloadSettingsPresets.description: Returns auto-download settings presets for the current user

getAutosaveSettings.description: Returns autosave settings for the current user

getAvailableChatBoostSlots.description: Returns the list of available chat boost slots for the current user

getAvailableGifts.description: Returns gifts that can be sent to other users and channel chats

getBackgroundUrl.description: Constructs a persistent HTTP URL for a background @name Background name @type Background type; backgroundTypeChatTheme isn't supported

getBankCardInfo.description: Returns information about a bank card @bank_card_number The bank card number

getBasicGroup.description: Returns information about a basic group by its identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot @basic_group_id Basic group identifier

getBasicGroupFullInfo.description: Returns full information about a basic group by its identifier @basic_group_id Basic group identifier

getBlockedMessageSenders.description: Returns users and chats that were blocked by the current user

block_list.description: Block list from which to return users

limit.description: The maximum number of users and chats to return; up to 100

offset.description: Number of users and chats to skip in the result; must be non-negative

getBotInfoDescription.description: Returns the text shown in the chat with a bot if the chat is empty in the given language. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code or an empty string

getBotInfoShortDescription.description: Returns the text shown on a bot's profile page and sent together with the link when users share the bot in the given language. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code or an empty string

getBotMediaPreviewInfo.description: Returns the list of media previews for the given language and the list of languages for which the bot has dedicated previews

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot. The bot must be owned and must have the main Web App

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code for which to get previews. If empty, then default previews are returned

getBotMediaPreviews.description: Returns the list of media previews of a bot @bot_user_id Identifier of the target bot. The bot must have the main Web App

getBotName.description: Returns the name of a bot in the given language. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code or an empty string

getBotSimilarBotCount.description: Returns approximate number of bots similar to the given bot

bot_user_id.description: User identifier of the target bot

return_local.description: Pass true to get the number of bots without sending network requests, or -1 if the number of bots is unknown locally

getBotSimilarBots.description: Returns a list of bots similar to the given bot @bot_user_id User identifier of the target bot

getBusinessAccountStarAmount.description: Returns the Telegram Star amount owned by a business account; for bots only @business_connection_id Unique identifier of business connection

getBusinessChatLinkInfo.description: Returns information about a business chat link @link_name Name of the link

getBusinessChatLinks.description: Returns business chat links created for the current account

getBusinessConnectedBot.description: Returns the business bot that is connected to the current user account. Returns a 404 error if there is no connected bot

getBusinessConnection.description: Returns information about a business connection by its identifier; for bots only @connection_id Identifier of the business connection to return

getBusinessFeatures.description: Returns information about features, available to Business users @source Source of the request; pass null if the method is called from settings or some non-standard source

getCallbackQueryAnswer.description: Sends a callback query to a bot and returns an answer. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat with the message

message_id.description: Identifier of the message from which the query originated. The message must not be scheduled

getCallbackQueryMessage.description: Returns information about a message with the callback button that originated a callback query; for bots only @chat_id Identifier of the chat the message belongs to @message_id Message identifier @callback_query_id Identifier of the callback query

getChat.description: Returns information about a chat by its identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatActiveStories.description: Returns the list of active stories posted by the given chat @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatAdministrators.description: Returns a list of administrators of the chat with their custom titles @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatArchivedStories.description: Returns the list of all stories posted by the given chat; requires can_edit_stories administrator right in the chat.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

from_story_id.description: Identifier of the story starting from which stories must be returned; use 0 to get results from the last story

limit.description: The maximum number of stories to be returned.

getChatAvailableMessageSenders.description: Returns the list of message sender identifiers, which can be used to send messages in a chat @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatAvailablePaidMessageReactionSende.description: Returns the list of message sender identifiers, which can be used to send a paid reaction in a chat @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatBoostFeatures.description: Returns the list of features available for different chat boost levels. This is an offline method

is_channel.description: Pass true to get the list of features for channels; pass false to get the list of features for supergroups

getChatBoostLevelFeatures.description: Returns the list of features available on the specific chat boost level. This is an offline method

is_channel.description: Pass true to get the list of features for channels; pass false to get the list of features for supergroups

getChatBoostLink.description: Returns an HTTPS link to boost the specified supergroup or channel chat @chat_id Identifier of the chat

getChatBoostLinkInfo.description: Returns information about a link to boost a chat. Can be called for any internal link of the type internalLinkTypeChatBoost @url The link to boost a chat

getChatBoostStatus.description: Returns the current boost status for a supergroup or a channel chat @chat_id Identifier of the chat

getChatBoosts.description: Returns the list of boosts applied to a chat; requires administrator rights in the chat

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

limit.description: The maximum number of boosts to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned boosts can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

only_gift_codes.description: Pass true to receive only boosts received from gift codes and giveaways created by the chat

getChatEventLog.description: Returns a list of service actions taken by chat members and administrators in the last 48 hours. Available only for supergroups and channels. Requires administrator rights. Returns results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing event_id)

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

filters.description: The types of events to return; pass null to get chat events of all types

from_event_id.description: Identifier of an event from which to return results. Use 0 to get results from the latest events

limit.description: The maximum number of events to return; up to 100

query.description: Search query by which to filter events

user_ids.description: User identifiers by which to filter events. By default, events relating to all users will be returned

getChatFolder.description: Returns information about a chat folder by its identifier @chat_folder_id Chat folder identifier

getChatFolderChatCount.description: Returns approximate number of chats in a being created chat folder. Main and archive chat lists must be fully preloaded for this function to work correctly @folder The new chat folder

getChatFolderChatsToLeave.description: Returns identifiers of pinned or always included chats from a chat folder, which are suggested to be left when the chat folder is deleted @chat_folder_id Chat folder identifier

getChatFolderDefaultIconName.description: Returns default icon name for a folder. Can be called synchronously @folder Chat folder

getChatFolderInviteLinks.description: Returns invite links created by the current user for a shareable chat folder @chat_folder_id Chat folder identifier

getChatFolderNewChats.description: Returns new chats added to a shareable chat folder by its owner. The method must be called at most once in getOption("chat_folder_new_chats_update_period") for the given chat folder @chat_folder_id Chat folder identifier

getChatHistory.description: Returns messages in a chat. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id).

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset.

offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number from -99 to -1 to get additionally -offset newer messages

only_local.description: Pass true to get only messages that are available without sending network requests

getChatInviteLink.description: Returns information about an invite link. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat to get own links and owner privileges to get other links

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

invite_link.description: Invite link to get

getChatInviteLinkCounts.description: Returns the list of chat administrators with number of their invite links. Requires owner privileges in the chat @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatInviteLinkMembers.description: Returns chat members joined a chat via an invite link. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

invite_link.description: Invite link for which to return chat members

limit.description: The maximum number of chat members to return; up to 100

offset_member.description: A chat member from which to return next chat members; pass null to get results from the beginning

only_with_expired_subscription.description: Pass true if the link is a subscription link and only members with expired subscription must be returned

getChatInviteLinks.description: Returns invite links for a chat created by specified administrator. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat to get own links and owner privileges to get other links

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

creator_user_id.description: User identifier of a chat administrator. Must be an identifier of the current user for non-owner

is_revoked.description: Pass true if revoked links needs to be returned instead of active or expired

limit.description: The maximum number of invite links to return; up to 100

offset_date.description: Creation date of an invite link starting after which to return invite links; use 0 to get results from the beginning

offset_invite_link.description: Invite link starting after which to return invite links; use empty string to get results from the beginning

getChatJoinRequests.description: Returns pending join requests in a chat

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

invite_link.description: Invite link for which to return join requests. If empty, all join requests will be returned. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links

limit.description: The maximum number of requests to join the chat to return

offset_request.description: A chat join request from which to return next requests; pass null to get results from the beginning

query.description: A query to search for in the first names, last names and usernames of the users to return

getChatListsToAddChat.description: Returns chat lists to which the chat can be added. This is an offline method @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatMember.description: Returns information about a single member of a chat @chat_id Chat identifier @member_id Member identifier

getChatMessageByDate.description: Returns the last message sent in a chat no later than the specified date. Returns a 404 error if such message doesn't exist

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages

getChatMessageCalendar.description: Returns information about the next messages of the specified type in the chat split by days. Returns the results in reverse chronological order. Can return partial result for the last returned day. Behavior of this method depends on the value of the option "utc_time_offset"

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which to return information about messages

filter.description: Filter for message content. Filters searchMessagesFilterEmpty, searchMessagesFilterMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadMention, and searchMessagesFilterUnreadReaction are unsupported in this function

from_message_id.description: The message identifier from which to return information about messages; use 0 to get results from the last message

topic_id.description: Pass topic identifier to get the result only in specific topic; pass null to get the result in all topics; forum topics and message threads aren't supported

getChatMessageCount.description: Returns approximate number of messages of the specified type in the chat or its topic

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which to count messages

filter.description: Filter for message content; searchMessagesFilterEmpty is unsupported in this function

return_local.description: Pass true to get the number of messages without sending network requests, or -1 if the number of messages is unknown locally

topic_id.description: Pass topic identifier to get number of messages only in specific topic; pass null to get number of messages in all topics; message threads aren't supported

getChatMessagePosition.description: Returns approximate 1-based position of a message among messages, which can be found by the specified filter in the chat and topic. Cannot be used in secret chats

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which to find message position

filter.description: Filter for message content; searchMessagesFilterEmpty, searchMessagesFilterUnreadMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadReaction, and searchMessagesFilterFailedToSend are unsupported in this function

message_id.description: Message identifier

topic_id.description: Pass topic identifier to get position among messages only in specific topic; pass null to get position among all chat messages; message threads aren't supported

getChatNotificationSettingsExceptions.description: Returns the list of chats with non-default notification settings for new messages

compare_sound.description: Pass true to include in the response chats with only non-default sound

scope.description: If specified, only chats from the scope will be returned; pass null to return chats from all scopes

getChatOwnerAfterLeaving.description: Returns the user who will become the owner of the chat after 7 days if the current user does not return to the chat during that period; requires owner privileges in the chat.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

getChatPinnedMessage.description: Returns information about a newest pinned message in the chat. Returns a 404 error if the message doesn't exist @chat_id Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

getChatPostedToChatPageStories.description: Returns the list of stories that posted by the given chat to its chat page. If from_story_id == 0, then pinned stories are returned first.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

from_story_id.description: Identifier of the story starting from which stories must be returned; use 0 to get results from pinned and the newest story

limit.description: The maximum number of stories to be returned.

getChatRevenueStatistics.description: Returns detailed revenue statistics about a chat. Currently, this method can be used only

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

is_dark.description: Pass true if a dark theme is used by the application

getChatRevenueTransactions.description: Returns the list of revenue transactions for a chat. Currently, this method can be used only

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

limit.description: The maximum number of transactions to be returned; up to 100

offset.description: Offset of the first transaction to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

getChatRevenueWithdrawalUrl.description: Returns a URL for chat revenue withdrawal; requires owner privileges in the channel chat or the bot. Currently, this method can be used only

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

password.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

getChatScheduledMessages.description: Returns all scheduled messages in a chat. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id) @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatSimilarChatCount.description: Returns approximate number of chats similar to the given chat

chat_id.description: Identifier of the target chat; must be an identifier of a channel chat

return_local.description: Pass true to get the number of chats without sending network requests, or -1 if the number of chats is unknown locally

getChatSimilarChats.description: Returns a list of chats similar to the given chat @chat_id Identifier of the target chat; must be an identifier of a channel chat

getChatSparseMessagePositions.description: Returns sparse positions of messages of the specified type in the chat to be used for shared media scroll implementation. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id).

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which to return information about message positions

filter.description: Filter for message content. Filters searchMessagesFilterEmpty, searchMessagesFilterMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadMention, and searchMessagesFilterUnreadReaction are unsupported in this function

from_message_id.description: The message identifier from which to return information about message positions

limit.description: The expected number of message positions to be returned; 50-2000. A smaller number of positions can be returned, if there are not enough appropriate messages

saved_messages_topic_id.description: If not 0, only messages in the specified Saved Messages topic will be considered; pass 0 to consider all messages, or for chats other than Saved Messages

getChatSponsoredMessages.description: Returns sponsored messages to be shown in a chat; for channel chats and chats with bots only @chat_id Identifier of the chat

getChatStatistics.description: Returns detailed statistics about a chat. Currently, this method can be used only for supergroups and channels. Can be used only if supergroupFullInfo.can_get_statistics == true @chat_id Chat identifier @is_dark Pass true if a dark theme is used by the application

getChatStoryAlbums.description: Returns the list of story albums owned by the given chat @chat_id Chat identifier

getChatStoryInteractions.description: Returns interactions with a story posted in a chat. Can be used only if story is posted on behalf of a chat and the user is an administrator in the chat

limit.description: The maximum number of story interactions to return

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

prefer_forwards.description: Pass true to get forwards and reposts first, then reactions, then other views; pass false to get interactions sorted just by interaction date

reaction_type.description: Pass the default heart reaction or a suggested reaction type to receive only interactions with the specified reaction type; pass null to receive all interactions; reactionTypePaid isn't supported

story_poster_chat_id.description: The identifier of the poster of the story

getChats.description: Returns an ordered list of chats from the beginning of a chat list. For informational purposes only. Use loadChats and updates processing instead to maintain chat lists in a consistent state

chat_list.description: The chat list in which to return chats; pass null to get chats from the main chat list

limit.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

getChatsForChatFolderInviteLink.description: Returns identifiers of chats from a chat folder, suitable for adding to a chat folder invite link @chat_folder_id Chat folder identifier

getChatsToPostStories.description: Returns supergroup and channel chats in which the current user has the right to post stories. The chats must be rechecked with canPostStory before actually trying to post a story there

getCloseFriends.description: Returns all close friends of the current user

getCollectibleItemInfo.description: Returns information about a given collectible item that was purchased at https://fragment.com

type.description: Type of the collectible item. The item must be used by a user and must be visible to the current user

getCommands.description: Returns the list of commands supported by the bot for the given user scope and language; for bots only

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code or an empty string

scope.description: The scope to which the commands are relevant; pass null to get commands in the default bot command scope

getConnectedAffiliateProgram.description: Returns an affiliate program that was connected to the given affiliate by identifier of the bot that created the program

affiliate.description: The affiliate to which the affiliate program will be connected

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot that created the program

getConnectedAffiliatePrograms.description: Returns affiliate programs that were connected to the given affiliate

affiliate.description: The affiliate to which the affiliate program were connected

limit.description: The maximum number of affiliate programs to return

offset.description: Offset of the first affiliate program to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

getConnectedWebsites.description: Returns all website where the current user used Telegram to log in

getContacts.description: Returns all contacts of the user

getCountries.description: Returns information about existing countries. Can be called before authorization

getCountryCode.description: Uses the current IP address to find the current country. Returns two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code. Can be called before authorization

getCountryFlagEmoji.description: Returns an emoji for the given country. Returns an empty string on failure. Can be called synchronously @country_code A two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code as received from getCountries

getCreatedPublicChats.description: Returns a list of public chats of the specified type, owned by the user @type Type of the public chats to return

getCurrentState.description: Returns all updates needed to restore current TDLib state, i.e. all actual updateAuthorizationState/updateUser/updateNewChat and others. This is especially useful if TDLib is run in a separate process. Can be called before initialization

getCurrentWeather.description: Returns the current weather in the given location @location The location

getCustomEmojiReactionAnimations.description: Returns TGS stickers with generic animations for custom emoji reactions

getCustomEmojiStickers.description: Returns the list of custom emoji stickers by their identifiers. Stickers are returned in arbitrary order. Only found stickers are returned

custom_emoji_ids.description: Identifiers of custom emoji stickers. At most 200 custom emoji stickers can be received simultaneously

getDeepLinkInfo.description: Returns information about a tg:// deep link. Use "tg://need_update_for_some_feature" or "tg:some_unsupported_feature" for testing. Returns a 404 error for unknown links. Can be called before authorization @link The link

getDefaultBackgroundCustomEmojiStickers.description: Returns default list of custom emoji stickers for reply background

getDefaultChatEmojiStatuses.description: Returns default emoji statuses for chats

getDefaultChatPhotoCustomEmojiStickers.description: Returns default list of custom emoji stickers for placing on a chat photo

getDefaultEmojiStatuses.description: Returns default emoji statuses for self status

getDefaultMessageAutoDeleteTime.description: Returns default message auto-delete time setting for new chats

getDefaultProfilePhotoCustomEmojiSticker.description: Returns default list of custom emoji stickers for placing on a profile photo

getDirectMessagesChatTopic.description: Returns information about the topic in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat

topic_id.description: Identifier of the topic to get

getDirectMessagesChatTopicHistory.description: Returns messages in the topic in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id)

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which messages must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset.
