offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number from -99 to -1 to get additionally -offset newer messages

topic_id.description: Identifier of the topic which messages will be fetched

getDirectMessagesChatTopicMessageByDate.description: Returns the last message sent in the topic in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user no later than the specified date

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat

date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages

topic_id.description: Identifier of the topic which messages will be fetched

getDirectMessagesChatTopicRevenue.description: Returns the total number of Telegram Stars received by the channel chat for direct messages from the given topic

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat administered by the current user

topic_id.description: Identifier of the topic

getDisallowedChatEmojiStatuses.description: Returns the list of emoji statuses, which can't be used as chat emoji status, even if they are from a sticker set with is_allowed_as_chat_emoji_status == true

getEmojiCategories.description: Returns available emoji categories @type Type of emoji categories to return; pass null to get default emoji categories

getEmojiReaction.description: Returns information about an emoji reaction. Returns a 404 error if the reaction is not found @emoji Text representation of the reaction

getEmojiSuggestionsUrl.description: Returns an HTTP URL which can be used to automatically log in to the translation platform and suggest new emoji replacements. The URL will be valid for 30 seconds after generation

language_code.description: Language code for which the emoji replacements will be suggested

getExternalLink.description: Returns an HTTP URL which can be used to automatically authorize the current user on a website after clicking an HTTP link.

allow_phone_number_access.description: Pass true if the current user allowed the bot that was returned in getExternalLinkInfo, to access their phone number

allow_write_access.description: Pass true if the current user allowed the bot that was returned in getExternalLinkInfo, to send them messages

getExternalLinkInfo.description: Returns information about an action to be done when the current user clicks an external link. Don't use this method for links from secret chats if link preview is disabled in secret chats @link The link

getFile.description: Returns information about a file. This is an offline method @file_id Identifier of the file to get

getFileDownloadedPrefixSize.description: Returns file downloaded prefix size from a given offset, in bytes @file_id Identifier of the file @offset Offset from which downloaded prefix size needs to be calculated

getFileExtension.description: Returns the extension of a file, guessed by its MIME type. Returns an empty string on failure. Can be called synchronously @mime_type The MIME type of the file

getFileMimeType.description: Returns the MIME type of a file, guessed by its extension. Returns an empty string on failure. Can be called synchronously @file_name The name of the file or path to the file

getForumTopic.description: Returns information about a topic in a forum supergroup chat or a chat with a bot with topics

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

getForumTopicDefaultIcons.description: Returns the list of custom emoji, which can be used as forum topic icon by all users

getForumTopicHistory.description: Returns messages in a topic in a forum supergroup chat or a chat with a bot with topics. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset.

offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number from -99 to -1 to get additionally -offset newer messages

getForumTopicLink.description: Returns an HTTPS link to a topic in a forum supergroup chat. This is an offline method @chat_id Identifier of the chat @forum_topic_id Forum topic identifier

getForumTopics.description: Returns found forum topics in a forum supergroup chat or a chat with a bot with topics. This is a temporary method for getting information about topic list from the server

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

limit.description: The maximum number of forum topics to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned forum topics is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset_date.description: The date starting from which the results need to be fetched. Use 0 or any date in the future to get results from the last topic

offset_forum_topic_id.description: The forum topic identifier of the last found topic, or 0 for the first request

offset_message_id.description: The message identifier of the last message in the last found topic, or 0 for the first request

query.description: Query to search for in the forum topic's name

getGameHighScores.description: Returns the high scores for a game and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only @chat_id The chat that contains the message with the game @message_id Identifier of the message @user_id User identifier

getGiftAuctionAcquiredGifts.description: Returns the gifts that were acquired by the current user on a gift auction @gift_id Identifier of the auctioned gift

getGiftAuctionState.description: Returns auction state for a gift @auction_id Unique identifier of the auction

getGiftChatThemes.description: Returns available to the current user gift chat themes

limit.description: The maximum number of chat themes to return

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

getGiftCollections.description: Returns collections of gifts owned by the given user or chat

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that received the gifts

getGiftUpgradePreview.description: Returns examples of possible upgraded gifts for a regular gift @regular_gift_id Identifier of the regular gift

getGiftsForCrafting.description: Returns upgraded gifts of the current user who can be used to craft another gifts

limit.description: The maximum number of gifts to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned objects is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

regular_gift_id.description: Identifier of the regular gift that will be used for crafting

chat_id.description: Identifier of the channel chat which started the giveaway

message_id.description: Identifier of the giveaway or a giveaway winners message in the chat

getGreetingStickers.description: Returns greeting stickers from regular sticker sets that can be used for the start page of other users

getGrossingWebAppBots.description: Returns the most grossing Web App bots

limit.description: The maximum number of bots to be returned; up to 100

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

getGroupCall.description: Returns information about a group call @group_call_id Group call identifier

getGroupCallParticipants.description: Returns information about participants of a non-joined group call that is not bound to a chat

input_group_call.description: The group call which participants will be returned

limit.description: The maximum number of participants to return; must be positive

getGroupCallStreamSegment.description: Returns a file with a segment of a video chat or live story in a modified OGG format for audio or MPEG-4 format for video

channel_id.description: Identifier of an audio/video channel to get as received from tgcalls

scale.description: Segment duration scale; 0-1. Segment's duration is 1000/(2**scale) milliseconds

time_offset.description: Point in time when the stream segment begins; Unix timestamp in milliseconds

video_quality.description: Video quality as received from tgcalls; pass null to get the worst available quality

getGroupCallStreams.description: Returns information about available streams in a video chat or a live story @group_call_id Group call identifier

getGroupsInCommon.description: Returns a list of common group chats with a given user. Chats are sorted by their type and creation date

limit.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 100

offset_chat_id.description: Chat identifier starting from which to return chats; use 0 for the first request

user_id.description: User identifier

getImportedContactCount.description: Returns the total number of imported contacts

getInactiveSupergroupChats.description: Returns a list of recently inactive supergroups and channels. Can be used when user reaches limit on the number of joined supergroups and channels and receives the error "CHANNELS_TOO_MUCH". Also, the limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

getInlineGameHighScores.description: Returns game high scores and some part of the high score table in the range of the specified user; for bots only @inline_message_id Inline message identifier @user_id User identifier

getInlineQueryResults.description: Sends an inline query to a bot and returns its results. Returns an error with code 502 if the bot fails to answer the query before the query timeout expires

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat where the query was sent

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

user_location.description: Location of the user; pass null if unknown or the bot doesn't need user's location

getInstalledBackgrounds.description: Returns backgrounds installed by the user @for_dark_theme Pass true to order returned backgrounds for a dark theme

getInstalledStickerSets.description: Returns a list of installed sticker sets @sticker_type Type of the sticker sets to return

getInternalLink.description: Returns an HTTPS or a tg: link with the given type. Can be called before authorization @type Expected type of the link @is_http Pass true to create an HTTPS link (only available for some link types); pass false to create a tg: link

getInternalLinkType.description: Returns information about the type of internal link. Returns a 404 error if the link is not internal. Can be called before authorization @link The link

getJsonString.description: Converts a JsonValue object to corresponding JSON-serialized string. Can be called synchronously @json_value The JsonValue object

getJsonValue.description: Converts a JSON-serialized string to corresponding JsonValue object. Can be called synchronously @json The JSON-serialized string

getKeywordEmojis.description: Returns emojis matching the keyword. Supported only if the file database is enabled. Order of results is unspecified

input_language_codes.description: List of possible IETF language tags of the user's input language; may be empty if unknown

text.description: Text to search for

getLanguagePackInfo.description: Returns information about a language pack. Returned language pack identifier may be different from a provided one. Can be called before authorization @language_pack_id Language pack identifier

getLanguagePackString.description: Returns a string stored in the local database from the specified localization target and language pack by its key. Returns a 404 error if the string is not found. Can be called synchronously

key.description: Language pack key of the string to be returned

language_pack_database_path.description: Path to the language pack database in which strings are stored

localization_target.description: Localization target to which the language pack belongs

getLanguagePackStrings.description: Returns strings from a language pack in the current localization target by their keys. Can be called before authorization

keys.description: Language pack keys of the strings to be returned; leave empty to request all available strings

language_pack_id.description: Language pack identifier of the strings to be returned

getLinkPreview.description: Returns a link preview by the text of a message. Do not call this function too often. Returns a 404 error if the text has no link preview

link_preview_options.description: Options to be used for generation of the link preview; pass null to use default link preview options

text.description: Message text with formatting

getLiveStoryAvailableMessageSenders.description: Returns the list of message sender identifiers, on whose behalf messages can be sent to a live story @group_call_id Group call identifier

getLiveStoryRtmpUrl.description: Returns RTMP URL for streaming to a live story; requires can_post_stories administrator right for channel chats @chat_id Chat identifier

getLiveStoryStreamer.description: Returns information about the user or the chat that streams to a live story; for live stories that aren't an RTMP stream only @group_call_id Group call identifier

getLiveStoryTopDonors.description: Returns the list of top live story donors @group_call_id Group call identifier of the live story

getLocalizationTargetInfo.description: Returns information about the current localization target. This is an offline method if only_local is true. Can be called before authorization @only_local Pass true to get only locally available information without sending network requests

getLogStream.description: Returns information about currently used log stream for internal logging of TDLib. Can be called synchronously

getLogTagVerbosityLevel.description: Returns current verbosity level for a specified TDLib internal log tag. Can be called synchronously @tag Logging tag to change verbosity level

getLogTags.description: Returns the list of available TDLib internal log tags, for example, ["actor", "binlog", "connections", "notifications", "proxy"]. Can be called synchronously

getLogVerbosityLevel.description: Returns current verbosity level of the internal logging of TDLib. Can be called synchronously

getLoginPasskeys.description: Returns the list of passkeys allowed to be used for the login by the current user

getLoginUrl.description: Returns an HTTP URL which can be used to automatically authorize the user on a website after clicking an inline button of type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeLoginUrl.

allow_write_access.description: Pass true to allow the bot to send messages to the current user. Phone number access can't be requested using the button

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the message with the button

message_id.description: Message identifier of the message with the button

getLoginUrlInfo.description: Returns information about a button of type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeLoginUrl. The method needs to be called when the user presses the button

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the message with the button

message_id.description: Message identifier of the message with the button. The message must not be scheduled

getMainWebApp.description: Returns information needed to open the main Web App of a bot

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot. If the bot is restricted for the current user, then show an error instead of calling the method

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which the Web App is opened; pass 0 if none

parameters.description: Parameters to use to open the Web App

getMapThumbnailFile.description: Returns information about a file with a map thumbnail in PNG format. Only map thumbnail files with size less than 1MB can be downloaded

chat_id.description: Identifier of a chat in which the thumbnail will be shown. Use 0 if unknown

height.description: Map height in pixels before applying scale; 16-1024

width.description: Map width in pixels before applying scale; 16-1024

getMarkdownText.description: Replaces text entities with Markdown formatting in a human-friendly format. Entities that can't be represented in Markdown unambiguously are kept as is. Can be called synchronously @text The text

getMenuButton.description: Returns menu button set by the bot for the given user; for bots only @user_id Identifier of the user or 0 to get the default menu button

getMessage.description: Returns information about a message. Returns a 404 error if the message doesn't exist

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

message_id.description: Identifier of the message to get

getMessageAddedReactions.description: Returns reactions added for a message, along with their sender

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

limit.description: The maximum number of reactions to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100

message_id.description: Identifier of the message. Use message.interaction_info.reactions.can_get_added_reactions to check whether added reactions can be received for the message

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

reaction_type.description: Type of the reactions to return; pass null to return all added reactions; reactionTypePaid isn't supported

getMessageAuthor.description: Returns information about actual author of a message sent on behalf of a channel. The method can be called if messageProperties.can_get_author == true

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getMessageAvailableReactions.description: Returns reactions, which can be added to a message. The list can change after updateActiveEmojiReactions, updateChatAvailableReactions for the chat, or updateMessageInteractionInfo for the message

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getMessageEffect.description: Returns information about a message effect. Returns a 404 error if the effect is not found @effect_id Unique identifier of the effect

getMessageEmbeddingCode.description: Returns an HTML code for embedding the message. Available only if messageProperties.can_get_embedding_code

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

for_album.description: Pass true to return an HTML code for embedding of the whole media album

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getMessageFileType.description: Returns information about a file with messages exported from another application @message_file_head Beginning of the message file; up to 100 first lines

getMessageImportConfirmationText.description: Returns a confirmation text to be shown to the user before starting message import

chat_id.description: Identifier of a chat to which the messages will be imported. It must be an identifier of a private chat with a mutual contact or an identifier of a supergroup chat with can_change_info member right

getMessageLink.description: Returns an HTTPS link to a message in a chat. Available only if messageProperties.can_get_link, or if messageProperties.can_get_media_timestamp_links and a media timestamp link is generated. This is an offline method

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

for_album.description: Pass true to create a link for the whole media album

in_message_thread.description: Pass true to create a link to the message as a channel post comment, in a message thread, or a forum topic

media_timestamp.description: If not 0, timestamp from which the video/audio/video note/voice note/story playing must start, in seconds. The media can be in the message content or in its link preview

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getMessageLinkInfo.description: Returns information about a public or private message link. Can be called for any internal link of the type internalLinkTypeMessage @url The message link

getMessageLocally.description: Returns information about a message, if it is available without sending network request. Returns a 404 error if message isn't available locally. This is an offline method

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

message_id.description: Identifier of the message to get

getMessageProperties.description: Returns properties of a message. This is an offline method @chat_id Chat identifier @message_id Identifier of the message

getMessagePublicForwards.description: Returns forwarded copies of a channel message to different public channels and public reposts as a story. Can be used only if messageProperties.can_get_statistics == true. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages and stories is chosen by TDLib

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages and stories to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned objects is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

message_id.description: Message identifier

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

getMessageReadDate.description: Returns read date of a recent outgoing message in a private chat. The method can be called if messageProperties.can_get_read_date == true

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getMessageStatistics.description: Returns detailed statistics about a message. Can be used only if messageProperties.can_get_statistics == true @chat_id Chat identifier @message_id Message identifier @is_dark Pass true if a dark theme is used by the application

getMessageThread.description: Returns information about a message thread. Can be used only if messageProperties.can_get_message_thread == true @chat_id Chat identifier @message_id Identifier of the message

getMessageThreadHistory.description: Returns messages in a message thread of a message. Can be used only if messageProperties.can_get_message_thread == true. Message thread of a channel message is in the channel's linked supergroup.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset.

message_id.description: Message identifier, which thread history needs to be returned

offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number from -99 to -1 to get additionally -offset newer messages

getMessageViewers.description: Returns viewers of a recent outgoing message in a basic group or a supergroup chat. For video notes and voice notes only users, opened content of the message, are returned. The method can be called if messageProperties.can_get_viewers == true

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getMessages.description: Returns information about messages. If a message is not found, returns null on the corresponding position of the result @chat_id Identifier of the chat the messages belong to @message_ids Identifiers of the messages to get

getNetworkStatistics.description: Returns network data usage statistics. Can be called before authorization @only_current Pass true to get statistics only for the current library launch

getNewChatPrivacySettings.description: Returns privacy settings for new chat creation

getOption.description: Returns the value of an option by its name. (Check the list of available options on https://core.telegram.org/tdlib/options.) Can be called before authorization. Can be called synchronously for options "version" and "commit_hash"

getOwnedBots.description: Returns the list of bots owned by the current user

getOwnedStickerSets.description: Returns sticker sets owned by the current user

limit.description: The maximum number of sticker sets to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned objects is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset_sticker_set_id.description: Identifier of the sticker set from which to return owned sticker sets; use 0 to get results from the beginning

getPaidMessageRevenue.description: Returns the total number of Telegram Stars received by the current user for paid messages from the given user @user_id Identifier of the user

getPasskeyParameters.description: Returns parameters for creating of a new passkey as JSON-serialized string

getPassportAuthorizationForm.description: Returns a Telegram Passport authorization form for sharing data with a service

bot_user_id.description: User identifier of the service's bot

nonce.description: Unique request identifier provided by the service

scope.description: Telegram Passport element types requested by the service

getPassportAuthorizationFormAvailableEle.description: Returns already available Telegram Passport elements suitable for completing a Telegram Passport authorization form. Result can be received only once for each authorization form

password.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

getPassportElement.description: Returns one of the available Telegram Passport elements @type Telegram Passport element type @password The 2-step verification password of the current user

getPasswordState.description: Returns the current state of 2-step verification

getPaymentForm.description: Returns an invoice payment form. This method must be called when the user presses inline button of the type inlineKeyboardButtonTypeBuy, or wants to buy access to media in a messagePaidMedia message

theme.description: Preferred payment form theme; pass null to use the default theme

getPaymentReceipt.description: Returns information about a successful payment @chat_id Chat identifier of the messagePaymentSuccessful message @message_id Message identifier

getPhoneNumberInfo.description: Returns information about a phone number by its prefix. Can be called before authorization @phone_number_prefix The phone number prefix

getPhoneNumberInfoSync.description: Returns information about a phone number by its prefix synchronously. getCountries must be called at least once after changing localization to the specified language if properly localized country information is expected. Can be called synchronously

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code for country information localization

getPollVoters.description: Returns message senders voted for the specified option in a non-anonymous polls. For optimal performance, the number of returned users is chosen by TDLib

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the poll belongs

limit.description: The maximum number of voters to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 50. For optimal performance, the number of returned voters is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the voter list has not been reached

message_id.description: Identifier of the message containing the poll

offset.description: Number of voters to skip in the result; must be non-negative

getPreferredCountryLanguage.description: Returns an IETF language tag of the language preferred in the country, which must be used to fill native fields in Telegram Passport personal details. Returns a 404 error if unknown @country_code A two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code

getPremiumFeatures.description: Returns information about features, available to Premium users @source Source of the request; pass null if the method is called from some non-standard source

getPremiumGiftPaymentOptions.description: Returns available options for gifting Telegram Premium to a user

getPremiumGiveawayPaymentOptions.description: Returns available options for creating of Telegram Premium giveaway or manual distribution of Telegram Premium among chat members

boosted_chat_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup or channel chat, which will be automatically boosted by receivers of the gift codes and which is administered by the user

getPremiumInfoSticker.description: Returns the sticker to be used as representation of the Telegram Premium subscription @month_count Number of months the Telegram Premium subscription will be active

getPremiumLimit.description: Returns information about a limit, increased for Premium users. Returns a 404 error if the limit is unknown @limit_type Type of the limit

getPremiumState.description: Returns state of Telegram Premium subscription and promotion videos for Premium features

getPremiumStickerExamples.description: Returns examples of premium stickers for demonstration purposes

getPremiumStickers.description: Returns premium stickers from regular sticker sets @limit The maximum number of stickers to be returned; 0-100

getPreparedInlineMessage.description: Saves an inline message to be sent by the given user

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot that created the message

getProxies.description: Returns the list of proxies that are currently set up. Can be called before authorization

getPublicPostSearchLimits.description: Checks public post search limits without actually performing the search @query Query that will be searched for

getPushReceiverId.description: Returns a globally unique push notification subscription identifier for identification of an account, which has received a push notification. Can be called synchronously @payload JSON-encoded push notification payload

getReadDatePrivacySettings.description: Returns privacy settings for message read date

getReceivedGift.description: Returns information about a received gift @received_gift_id Identifier of the gift

getReceivedGifts.description: Returns gifts received by the given user or chat

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request; for bots only

collection_id.description: Pass collection identifier to get gifts only from the specified collection; pass 0 to get gifts regardless of collections

exclude_hosted.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that are just hosted and are not owned by the owner

exclude_non_upgradable.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that can be purchased limited number of times and can't be upgraded

exclude_saved.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that are saved to the chat's profile page. Always false for gifts received by other users and channel chats without can_post_messages administrator right

exclude_unlimited.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that can be purchased unlimited number of times

exclude_unsaved.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that aren't saved to the chat's profile page. Always true for gifts received by other users and channel chats without can_post_messages administrator right

exclude_upgradable.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that can be purchased limited number of times and can be upgraded

exclude_upgraded.description: Pass true to exclude upgraded gifts

exclude_without_colors.description: Pass true to exclude gifts that can't be used in setUpgradedGiftColors

limit.description: The maximum number of gifts to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned objects is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

owner_id.description: Identifier of the gift receiver

sort_by_price.description: Pass true to sort results by gift price instead of send date

getRecentEmojiStatuses.description: Returns recent emoji statuses for self status

getRecentInlineBots.description: Returns up to 20 recently used inline bots in the order of their last usage

getRecentStickers.description: Returns a list of recently used stickers @is_attached Pass true to return stickers and masks that were recently attached to photos or video files; pass false to return recently sent stickers

getRecentlyOpenedChats.description: Returns recently opened chats. This is an offline method. Returns chats in the order of last opening @limit The maximum number of chats to be returned

getRecentlyVisitedTMeUrls.description: Returns t.me URLs recently visited by a newly registered user @referrer Google Play referrer to identify the user

getRecommendedChatFolders.description: Returns recommended chat folders for the current user

getRecommendedChats.description: Returns a list of channel chats recommended to the current user

getRecoveryEmailAddress.description: Returns a 2-step verification recovery email address that was previously set up. This method can be used to verify a password provided by the user @password The 2-step verification password for the current user

getRemoteFile.description: Returns information about a file by its remote identifier. This is an offline method. Can be used to register a URL as a file for further uploading, or sending as a message. Even the request succeeds, the file can be used only if it is still accessible to the user.

file_type.description: File type; pass null if unknown

remote_file_id.description: Remote identifier of the file to get

getRepliedMessage.description: Returns information about a non-bundled message that is replied by a given message. Also, returns the pinned message for messagePinMessage,

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat the message belongs to

message_id.description: Identifier of the reply message

getSavedMessagesTags.description: Returns tags used in Saved Messages or a Saved Messages topic

saved_messages_topic_id.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which tags will be returned; pass 0 to get all Saved Messages tags

getSavedMessagesTopicHistory.description: Returns messages in a Saved Messages topic. The messages are returned in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id)

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which messages must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than or equal to -offset.

offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number from -99 to -1 to get additionally -offset newer messages

saved_messages_topic_id.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which messages will be fetched

getSavedMessagesTopicMessageByDate.description: Returns the last message sent in a Saved Messages topic no later than the specified date

date.description: Point in time (Unix timestamp) relative to which to search for messages

saved_messages_topic_id.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic which message will be returned

getSavedNotificationSound.description: Returns saved notification sound by its identifier. Returns a 404 error if there is no saved notification sound with the specified identifier @notification_sound_id Identifier of the notification sound

getSavedNotificationSounds.description: Returns the list of saved notification sounds. If a sound isn't in the list, then default sound needs to be used

getSavedOrderInfo.description: Returns saved order information. Returns a 404 error if there is no saved order information

getScopeNotificationSettings.description: Returns the notification settings for chats of a given type @scope Types of chats for which to return the notification settings information

getSearchSponsoredChats.description: Returns sponsored chats to be shown in the search results @query Query the user searches for

getSearchedForTags.description: Returns recently searched for hashtags or cashtags by their prefix @tag_prefix Prefix of hashtags or cashtags to return @limit The maximum number of items to be returned

getSecretChat.description: Returns information about a secret chat by its identifier. This is an offline method @secret_chat_id Secret chat identifier

getStakeDiceState.description: Returns the current state of stake dice

getStarAdAccountUrl.description: Returns a URL for a Telegram Ad platform account that can be used to set up advertisements for the chat paid in the owned Telegram Stars

owner_id.description: Identifier of the owner of the Telegram Stars; can be identifier of an owned bot, or identifier of an owned channel chat

getStarGiftPaymentOptions.description: Returns available options for Telegram Stars gifting @user_id Identifier of the user who will receive Telegram Stars; pass 0 to get options for an unspecified user

getStarGiveawayPaymentOptions.description: Returns available options for Telegram Star giveaway creation

getStarPaymentOptions.description: Returns available options for Telegram Stars purchase

getStarRevenueStatistics.description: Returns detailed Telegram Star revenue statistics

is_dark.description: Pass true if a dark theme is used by the application

owner_id.description: Identifier of the owner of the Telegram Stars; can be identifier of the current user, an owned bot, or a supergroup or a channel chat with supergroupFullInfo.can_get_star_revenue_statistics == true

getStarSubscriptions.description: Returns the list of Telegram Star subscriptions for the current user

offset.description: Offset of the first subscription to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

only_expiring.description: Pass true to receive only expiring subscriptions for which there are no enough Telegram Stars to extend

getStarTransactions.description: Returns the list of Telegram Star transactions for the specified owner

direction.description: Direction of the transactions to receive; pass null to get all transactions

limit.description: The maximum number of transactions to return

offset.description: Offset of the first transaction to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

owner_id.description: Identifier of the owner of the Telegram Stars; can be the identifier of the current user, identifier of an owned bot,

subscription_id.description: If non-empty, only transactions related to the Star Subscription will be returned

getStarWithdrawalUrl.description: Returns a URL for Telegram Star withdrawal

owner_id.description: Identifier of the owner of the Telegram Stars; can be identifier of the current user, an owned bot, or an owned supergroup or channel chat

password.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars to withdraw; must be between getOption("star_withdrawal_count_min") and getOption("star_withdrawal_count_max")

getStatisticalGraph.description: Loads an asynchronous or a zoomed in statistical graph @chat_id Chat identifier @token The token for graph loading @x X-value for zoomed in graph or 0 otherwise

getStickerEmojis.description: Returns emoji corresponding to a sticker. The list is only for informational purposes, because a sticker is always sent with a fixed emoji from the corresponding Sticker object @sticker Sticker file identifier

getStickerOutline.description: Returns outline of a sticker. This is an offline method. Returns a 404 error if the outline isn't known

for_animated_emoji.description: Pass true to get the outline scaled for animated emoji

for_clicked_animated_emoji_message.description: Pass true to get the outline scaled for clicked animated emoji message

getStickerOutlineSvgPath.description: Returns outline of a sticker as an SVG path. This is an offline method. Returns an empty string if the outline isn't known

for_animated_emoji.description: Pass true to get the outline scaled for animated emoji

for_clicked_animated_emoji_message.description: Pass true to get the outline scaled for clicked animated emoji message

getStickerSet.description: Returns information about a sticker set by its identifier @set_id Identifier of the sticker set

getStickerSetName.description: Returns name of a sticker set by its identifier @set_id Identifier of the sticker set

getStickers.description: Returns stickers from the installed sticker sets that correspond to any of the given emoji or can be found by sticker-specific keywords. If the query is non-empty, then favorite, recently used or trending stickers may also be returned

chat_id.description: Chat identifier for which to return stickers. Available custom emoji stickers may be different for different chats

limit.description: The maximum number of stickers to be returned

query.description: Search query; a space-separated list of emojis or a keyword prefix. If empty, returns all known installed stickers

sticker_type.description: Type of the stickers to return

getStorageStatistics.description: Returns storage usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

chat_limit.description: The maximum number of chats with the largest storage usage for which separate statistics need to be returned. All other chats will be grouped in entries with chat_id == 0. If the chat info database is not used, the chat_limit is ignored and is always set to 0

getStorageStatisticsFast.description: Quickly returns approximate storage usage statistics. Can be called before authorization

only_local.description: Pass true to get only locally available information without sending network requests

story_poster_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that posted the story

getStoryAlbumStories.description: Returns the list of stories added to the given story album. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

limit.description: The maximum number of stories to be returned. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return; use 0 to get results from the first album story

getStoryAvailableReactions.description: Returns reactions, which can be chosen for a story @row_size Number of reaction per row, 5-25

getStoryInteractions.description: Returns interactions with a story. The method can be called only for stories posted on behalf of the current user

limit.description: The maximum number of story interactions to return

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

only_contacts.description: Pass true to get only interactions by contacts; pass false to get all relevant interactions

prefer_forwards.description: Pass true to get forwards and reposts first, then reactions, then other views; pass false to get interactions sorted just by interaction date

prefer_with_reaction.description: Pass true to get interactions with reaction first; pass false to get interactions sorted just by interaction date. Ignored if prefer_forwards == true

query.description: Query to search for in names, usernames and titles; may be empty to get all relevant interactions

getStoryNotificationSettingsExceptions.description: Returns the list of chats with non-default notification settings for stories

getStoryPublicForwards.description: Returns forwards of a story as a message to public chats and reposts by public channels. Can be used only if the story is posted on behalf of the current user or story.can_get_statistics == true.

limit.description: The maximum number of messages and stories to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned objects is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

story_poster_chat_id.description: The identifier of the poster of the story

getStoryStatistics.description: Returns detailed statistics about a story. Can be used only if story.can_get_statistics == true @chat_id Chat identifier @story_id Story identifier @is_dark Pass true if a dark theme is used by the application

getSuggestedFileName.description: Returns suggested name for saving a file in a given directory @file_id Identifier of the file @directory Directory in which the file is expected to be saved

getSuggestedStickerSetName.description: Returns a suggested name for a new sticker set with a given title @title Sticker set title; 1-64 characters

getSuitableDiscussionChats.description: Returns a list of basic group and supergroup chats, which can be used as a discussion group for a channel. Returned basic group chats must be first upgraded to supergroups before they can be set as a discussion group.

getSuitablePersonalChats.description: Returns a list of channel chats, which can be used as a personal chat

getSupergroup.description: Returns information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot @supergroup_id Supergroup or channel identifier

getSupergroupFullInfo.description: Returns full information about a supergroup or a channel by its identifier, cached for up to 1 minute @supergroup_id Supergroup or channel identifier

getSupergroupMembers.description: Returns information about members or banned users in a supergroup or channel. Can be used only if supergroupFullInfo.can_get_members == true; additionally, administrator privileges may be required for some filters

filter.description: The type of users to return; pass null to use supergroupMembersFilterRecent

limit.description: The maximum number of users to be returned; up to 200

offset.description: Number of users to skip

supergroup_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup or channel

getSupportName.description: Returns localized name of the Telegram support user; for Telegram support only

getSupportUser.description: Returns a user who can be contacted to get support

getTemporaryPasswordState.description: Returns information about the current temporary password

getTextEntities.description: Returns all entities (mentions, hashtags, cashtags, bot commands, bank card numbers, URLs, and email addresses) found in the text. Can be called synchronously @text The text in which to look for entities

getThemeParametersJsonString.description: Converts a themeParameters object to corresponding JSON-serialized string. Can be called synchronously @theme Theme parameters to convert to JSON

getThemedChatEmojiStatuses.description: Returns up to 8 emoji statuses, which must be shown in the emoji status list for chats

getThemedEmojiStatuses.description: Returns up to 8 emoji statuses, which must be shown right after the default Premium Badge in the emoji status list for self status

getTimeZones.description: Returns the list of supported time zones

getTonRevenueStatistics.description: Returns detailed Toncoin revenue statistics of the current user @is_dark Pass true if a dark theme is used by the application

getTonTransactions.description: Returns the list of Toncoin transactions of the current user

direction.description: Direction of the transactions to receive; pass null to get all transactions

limit.description: The maximum number of transactions to return

offset.description: Offset of the first transaction to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

getTonWithdrawalUrl.description: Returns a URL for Toncoin withdrawal from the current user's account. The user must have at least 10 toncoins to withdraw

password.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

getTopChats.description: Returns a list of frequently used chats @category Category of chats to be returned @limit The maximum number of chats to be returned; up to 30

getTrendingStickerSets.description: Returns a list of trending sticker sets. For optimal performance, the number of returned sticker sets is chosen by TDLib

limit.description: The maximum number of sticker sets to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned sticker sets is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list has not been reached

offset.description: The offset from which to return the sticker sets; must be non-negative

sticker_type.description: Type of the sticker sets to return

getUpgradedGift.description: Returns information about an upgraded gift by its name @name Unique name of the upgraded gift

getUpgradedGiftEmojiStatuses.description: Returns available upgraded gift emoji statuses for self status

getUpgradedGiftValueInfo.description: Returns information about value of an upgraded gift by its name @name Unique name of the upgraded gift

getUpgradedGiftVariants.description: Returns all possible variants of upgraded gifts for a regular gift

return_craft_models.description: Pass true to get models that can be obtained by crafting a gift from upgraded gifts

return_upgrade_models.description: Pass true to get models that can be obtained by upgrading a regular gift

getUpgradedGiftWithdrawalUrl.description: Returns a URL for upgraded gift withdrawal in the TON blockchain as an NFT; requires owner privileges for gifts owned by a chat

password.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

getUpgradedGiftsPromotionalAnimation.description: Returns promotional anumation for upgraded gifts

getUser.description: Returns information about a user by their identifier. This is an offline method if the current user is not a bot @user_id User identifier

getUserChatBoosts.description: Returns the list of boosts applied to a chat by a given user; requires administrator rights in the chat; for bots only

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

user_id.description: Identifier of the user

getUserFullInfo.description: Returns full information about a user by their identifier @user_id User identifier

getUserLink.description: Returns an HTTPS link, which can be used to get information about the current user

getUserPrivacySettingRules.description: Returns the current privacy settings @setting The privacy setting

getUserProfileAudios.description: Returns the list of profile audio files of a user

limit.description: The maximum number of audio files to be returned; up to 100

offset.description: The number of audio files to skip; must be non-negative

user_id.description: User identifier

getUserProfilePhotos.description: Returns the profile photos of a user. Personal and public photo aren't returned

limit.description: The maximum number of photos to be returned; up to 100

offset.description: The number of photos to skip; must be non-negative

user_id.description: User identifier

getUserSupportInfo.description: Returns support information for the given user; for Telegram support only @user_id User identifier

getVideoChatAvailableParticipants.description: Returns the list of participant identifiers, on whose behalf a video chat in the chat can be joined @chat_id Chat identifier

getVideoChatInviteLink.description: Returns invite link to a video chat in a public chat

can_self_unmute.description: Pass true if the invite link needs to contain an invite hash, passing which to joinVideoChat would allow the invited user to unmute themselves. Requires groupCall.can_be_managed right

getVideoChatRtmpUrl.description: Returns RTMP URL for streaming to the video chat of a chat; requires can_manage_video_chats administrator right @chat_id Chat identifier

getVideoMessageAdvertisements.description: Returns advertisements to be shown while a video from a message is watched. Available only if messageProperties.can_get_video_advertisements

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat with the message

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

getWebAppLinkUrl.description: Returns an HTTPS URL of a Web App to open after a link of the type internalLinkTypeWebApp is clicked

allow_write_access.description: Pass true if the current user allowed the bot to send them messages

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which the link was clicked; pass 0 if none

parameters.description: Parameters to use to open the Web App

web_app_short_name.description: Short name of the Web App

getWebAppPlaceholder.description: Returns a default placeholder for Web Apps of a bot. This is an offline method. Returns a 404 error if the placeholder isn't known @bot_user_id Identifier of the target bot

getWebAppUrl.description: Returns an HTTPS URL of a Web App to open from the side menu, a keyboardButtonTypeWebApp button, or an inlineQueryResultsButtonTypeWebApp button

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot. If the bot is restricted for the current user, then show an error instead of calling the method

parameters.description: Parameters to use to open the Web App

url.description: The URL from a keyboardButtonTypeWebApp button, inlineQueryResultsButtonTypeWebApp button, or an empty string when the bot is opened from the side menu

getWebPageInstantView.description: Returns an instant view version of a web page if available. This is an offline method if only_local is true. Returns a 404 error if the web page has no instant view page

only_local.description: Pass true to get only locally available information without sending network requests

url.description: The web page URL

giftPremiumWithStars.description: Allows to buy a Telegram Premium subscription for another user with payment in Telegram Stars; for bots only

month_count.description: Number of months the Telegram Premium subscription will be active for the user

star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars to pay for subscription

text.description: Text to show to the user receiving Telegram Premium; 0-getOption("gift_text_length_max") characters. Only Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough, Spoiler, and CustomEmoji entities are allowed

user_id.description: Identifier of the user which will receive Telegram Premium

hideContactCloseBirthdays.description: Hides the list of contacts that have close birthdays for 24 hours

hideSuggestedAction.description: Hides a suggested action @action Suggested action to hide

importContacts.description: Adds new contacts or edits existing contacts by their phone numbers; contacts' user identifiers are ignored

contacts.description: The list of contacts to import or edit

importMessages.description: Imports messages exported from another app

attached_files.description: Files used in the imported messages. Only inputFileLocal and inputFileGenerated are supported. The files must not be previously uploaded

chat_id.description: Identifier of a chat to which the messages will be imported. It must be an identifier of a private chat with a mutual contact or an identifier of a supergroup chat with can_change_info member right

message_file.description: File with messages to import. Only inputFileLocal and inputFileGenerated are supported. The file must not be previously uploaded

increaseGiftAuctionBid.description: Increases a bid for an auction gift without changing gift text and receiver

gift_id.description: Identifier of the gift to put the bid on

star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars to put in the bid

inviteGroupCallParticipant.description: Invites a user to an active group call; for group calls not bound to a chat only. Sends a service message of the type messageGroupCall.

is_video.description: Pass true if the group call is a video call

user_id.description: User identifier

inviteVideoChatParticipants.description: Invites users to an active video chat. Sends a service message of the type messageInviteVideoChatParticipants to the chat bound to the group call

user_ids.description: User identifiers. At most 10 users can be invited simultaneously

isLoginEmailAddressRequired.description: Checks whether the current user is required to set login email address

isProfileAudio.description: Checks whether a file is in the profile audio files of the current user. Returns a 404 error if it isn't @file_id Identifier of the audio file to check

joinChat.description: Adds the current user as a new member to a chat. Private and secret chats can't be joined using this method. May return an error with a message "INVITE_REQUEST_SENT" if only a join request was created @chat_id Chat identifier

joinChatByInviteLink.description: Uses an invite link to add the current user to the chat if possible. May return an error with a message "INVITE_REQUEST_SENT" if only a join request was created @invite_link Invite link to use

joinGroupCall.description: Joins a regular group call that is not bound to a chat @input_group_call The group call to join @join_parameters Parameters to join the call

joinLiveStory.description: Joins a group call of an active live story. Returns join response payload for tgcalls

joinVideoChat.description: Joins an active video chat. Returns join response payload for tgcalls

invite_hash.description: Invite hash as received from internalLinkTypeVideoChat

participant_id.description: Identifier of a group call participant, which will be used to join the call; pass null to join as self

giveaway_id.description: Unique identifier of the prepaid giveaway

star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars to be distributed through the giveaway; pass 0 for Telegram Premium giveaways

winner_count.description: The number of users to receive giveaway prize

leaveChat.description: Removes the current user from chat members. Private and secret chats can't be left using this method @chat_id Chat identifier

leaveGroupCall.description: Leaves a group call @group_call_id Group call identifier

loadActiveStories.description: Loads more active stories from a story list. The loaded stories will be sent through updates. Active stories are sorted by

story_list.description: The story list in which to load active stories

loadChats.description: Loads more chats from a chat list. The loaded chats and their positions in the chat list will be sent through updates. Chats are sorted by the pair (chat.position.order, chat.id) in descending order. Returns a 404 error if all chats have been loaded

chat_list.description: The chat list in which to load chats; pass null to load chats from the main chat list

limit.description: The maximum number of chats to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded chats is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

loadDirectMessagesChatTopics.description: Loads more topics in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user. The loaded topics will be sent through updateDirectMessagesChatTopic.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat

limit.description: The maximum number of topics to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded topics is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

loadGroupCallParticipants.description: Loads more participants of a group call; not supported in live stories. The loaded participants will be received through updates.

group_call_id.description: Group call identifier. The group call must be previously received through getGroupCall and must be joined or being joined

limit.description: The maximum number of participants to load; up to 100

loadQuickReplyShortcutMessages.description: Loads quick reply messages that can be sent by a given quick reply shortcut. The loaded messages will be sent through updateQuickReplyShortcutMessages

shortcut_id.description: Unique identifier of the quick reply shortcut

loadQuickReplyShortcuts.description: Loads quick reply shortcuts created by the current user. The loaded data will be sent through updateQuickReplyShortcut and updateQuickReplyShortcuts

loadSavedMessagesTopics.description: Loads more Saved Messages topics. The loaded topics will be sent through updateSavedMessagesTopic. Topics are sorted by their topic.order in descending order. Returns a 404 error if all topics have been loaded

limit.description: The maximum number of topics to be loaded. For optimal performance, the number of loaded topics is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit, even if the end of the list is not reached

logOut.description: Closes the TDLib instance after a proper logout. Requires an available network connection. All local data will be destroyed. After the logout completes, updateAuthorizationState with authorizationStateClosed will be sent

markChecklistTasksAsDone.description: Adds tasks of a checklist in a message as done or not done

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat with the message

marked_as_done_task_ids.description: Identifiers of tasks that were marked as done

marked_as_not_done_task_ids.description: Identifiers of tasks that were marked as not done

message_id.description: Identifier of the message containing the checklist. Use messageProperties.can_mark_tasks_as_done to check whether the tasks can be marked as done or not done

openBotSimilarBot.description: Informs TDLib that a bot was opened from the list of similar bots

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the original bot, which similar bots were requested

openChat.description: Informs TDLib that the chat is opened by the user. Many useful activities depend on the chat being opened or closed (e.g., in supergroups and channels all updates are received only for opened chats) @chat_id Chat identifier

openChatSimilarChat.description: Informs TDLib that a chat was opened from the list of similar chats. The method is independent of openChat and closeChat methods

chat_id.description: Identifier of the original chat, which similar chats were requested

openGiftAuction.description: Informs TDLib that a gift auction was opened by the user @gift_id Identifier of the gift, which auction was opened

openMessageContent.description: Informs TDLib that the message content has been opened (e.g., the user has opened a photo, video, document, location or venue, or has listened to an audio file or voice note message).

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the message

message_id.description: Identifier of the message with the opened content

openSponsoredChat.description: Informs TDLib that the user opened a sponsored chat @sponsored_chat_unique_id Unique identifier of the sponsored chat

openStory.description: Informs TDLib that a story is opened and is being viewed by the user

story_poster_chat_id.description: The identifier of the chat that posted the opened story

openWebApp.description: Informs TDLib that a Web App is being opened from the attachment menu, a botMenuButton button, an internalLinkTypeAttachmentMenuBot link, or an inlineKeyboardButtonTypeWebApp button.

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot, providing the Web App. If the bot is restricted for the current user, then show an error instead of calling the method

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which the Web App is opened. The Web App can't be opened in secret chats

parameters.description: Parameters to use to open the Web App

reply_to.description: Information about the message or story to be replied in the message sent by the Web App; pass null if none

topic_id.description: Topic in which the message will be sent; pass null if none

url.description: The URL from an inlineKeyboardButtonTypeWebApp button, a botMenuButton button, an internalLinkTypeAttachmentMenuBot link, or an empty string otherwise

optimizeStorage.description: Optimizes storage usage, i.e. deletes some files and returns new storage usage statistics. Secret thumbnails can't be deleted

chat_ids.description: If non-empty, only files from the given chats are considered. Use 0 as chat identifier to delete files not belonging to any chat (e.g., profile photos)

chat_limit.description: Same as in getStorageStatistics. Affects only returned statistics

count.description: Limit on the total number of files after deletion. Pass -1 to use the default limit

exclude_chat_ids.description: If non-empty, files from the given chats are excluded. Use 0 as chat identifier to exclude all files not belonging to any chat (e.g., profile photos)

file_types.description: If non-empty, only files with the given types are considered. By default, all types except thumbnails, profile photos, stickers and wallpapers are deleted

immunity_delay.description: The amount of time after the creation of a file during which it can't be deleted, in seconds. Pass -1 to use the default value

return_deleted_file_statistics.description: Pass true if statistics about the files that were deleted must be returned instead of the whole storage usage statistics. Affects only returned statistics

size.description: Limit on the total size of files after deletion, in bytes. Pass -1 to use the default limit

ttl.description: Limit on the time that has passed since the last time a file was accessed (or creation time for some filesystems). Pass -1 to use the default limit

parseMarkdown.description: Parses Markdown entities in a human-friendly format, ignoring markup errors. Can be called synchronously

text.description: The text to parse. For example, "__italic__ ~~strikethrough~~ ||spoiler|| **bold** `code` ```pre``` __[italic__ text_url](telegram.org) __italic**bold italic__bold**"

parseTextEntities.description: Parses Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough, Spoiler, CustomEmoji, BlockQuote, ExpandableBlockQuote, Code, Pre, PreCode, TextUrl

text.description: The text to parse

pinChatMessage.description: Pins a message in a chat. A message can be pinned only if messageProperties.can_be_pinned

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

disable_notification.description: Pass true to disable notification about the pinned message. Notifications are always disabled in channels and private chats

message_id.description: Identifier of the new pinned message

only_for_self.description: Pass true to pin the message only for self; private chats only

pingProxy.description: Computes time needed to receive a response from a Telegram server through a proxy. Can be called before authorization

proxy.description: The proxy to test; pass null to ping a Telegram server without a proxy

placeGiftAuctionBid.description: Places a bid on an auction gift

gift_id.description: Identifier of the gift to place the bid on

is_private.description: Pass true to show gift text and sender only to the gift receiver; otherwise, everyone will be able to see them

star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars to place in the bid

text.description: Text to show along with the gift; 0-getOption("gift_text_length_max") characters. Only Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough, Spoiler, and CustomEmoji entities are allowed.

user_id.description: Identifier of the user who will receive the gift

postStory.description: Posts a new story on behalf of a chat; requires can_post_stories administrator right for supergroup and channel chats. Returns a temporary story

active_period.description: Period after which the story is moved to archive, in seconds; must be one of 6 * 3600, 12 * 3600, 86400, or 2 * 86400 for Telegram Premium users, and 86400 otherwise

album_ids.description: Identifiers of story albums to which the story will be added upon posting. An album can have up to getOption("story_album_size_max") stories

areas.description: Clickable rectangle areas to be shown on the story media; pass null if none

caption.description: Story caption; pass null to use an empty caption; 0-getOption("story_caption_length_max") characters; can have entities only if getOption("can_use_text_entities_in_story_caption")

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that will post the story. Pass Saved Messages chat identifier when posting a story on behalf of the current user

from_story_full_id.description: Full identifier of the original story, which content was used to create the story; pass null if the story isn't repost of another story

is_posted_to_chat_page.description: Pass true to keep the story accessible after expiration

privacy_settings.description: The privacy settings for the story; ignored for stories posted on behalf of supergroup and channel chats

protect_content.description: Pass true if the content of the story must be protected from forwarding and screenshotting

preliminaryUploadFile.description: Preliminarily uploads a file to the cloud before sending it in a message, which can be useful for uploading of being recorded voice and video notes.

file_type.description: File type; pass null if unknown

priority.description: Priority of the upload (1-32). The higher the priority, the earlier the file will be uploaded. If the priorities of two files are equal, then the first one for which preliminaryUploadFile was called will be uploaded first

processChatFolderNewChats.description: Process new chats added to a shareable chat folder by its owner @chat_folder_id Chat folder identifier @added_chat_ids Identifiers of the new chats, which are added to the chat folder. The chats are automatically joined if they aren't joined yet

processChatJoinRequest.description: Handles a pending join request in a chat @chat_id Chat identifier @user_id Identifier of the user who sent the request @approve Pass true to approve the request; pass false to decline it

processChatJoinRequests.description: Handles all pending join requests for a given link in a chat

approve.description: Pass true to approve all requests; pass false to decline them

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

invite_link.description: Invite link for which to process join requests. If empty, all join requests will be processed. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links

processGiftPurchaseOffer.description: Handles a pending gift purchase offer

accept.description: Pass true to accept the request; pass false to reject it

message_id.description: Identifier of the message with the gift purchase offer

processPushNotification.description: Handles a push notification. Returns error with code 406 if the push notification is not supported and connection to the server is required to fetch new data. Can be called before authorization

payload.description: JSON-encoded push notification payload with all fields sent by the server, and "google.sent_time" and "google.notification.sound" fields added

rateSpeechRecognition.description: Rates recognized speech in a video note or a voice note message @chat_id Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs @message_id Identifier of the message @is_good Pass true if the speech recognition is good

readAllChatMentions.description: Marks all mentions in a chat as read @chat_id Chat identifier

readAllChatReactions.description: Marks all reactions in a chat as read @chat_id Chat identifier

readAllDirectMessagesChatTopicReactions.description: Removes all unread reactions in the topic in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

topic_id.description: Topic identifier

readAllForumTopicMentions.description: Marks all mentions in a topic in a forum supergroup chat as read

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

forum_topic_id.description: Forum topic identifier in which mentions are marked as read

readAllForumTopicReactions.description: Marks all reactions in a topic in a forum supergroup chat or a chat with a bot with topics as read

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

forum_topic_id.description: Forum topic identifier in which reactions are marked as read

readBusinessMessage.description: Reads a message on behalf of a business account; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection through which the message was received

chat_id.description: The chat the message belongs to

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

readChatList.description: Traverses all chats in a chat list and marks all messages in the chats as read @chat_list Chat list in which to mark all chats as read

readFilePart.description: Reads a part of a file from the TDLib file cache and returns read bytes. This method is intended to be used only if the application has no direct access to TDLib's file system, because it is usually slower than a direct read from the file

count.description: Number of bytes to read. An error will be returned if there are not enough bytes available in the file from the specified position. Pass 0 to read all available data from the specified position

file_id.description: Identifier of the file. The file must be located in the TDLib file cache

offset.description: The offset from which to read the file

readdQuickReplyShortcutMessages.description: Readds quick reply messages which failed to add. Can be called only for messages for which messageSendingStateFailed.can_retry is true and after specified in messageSendingStateFailed.retry_after time passed.

message_ids.description: Identifiers of the quick reply messages to readd. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order

recognizeSpeech.description: Recognizes speech in a video note or a voice note message

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

message_id.description: Identifier of the message. Use messageProperties.can_recognize_speech to check whether the message is suitable

recoverAuthenticationPassword.description: Recovers the 2-step verification password with a password recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

new_hint.description: New password hint; may be empty

new_password.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

recoverPassword.description: Recovers the 2-step verification password using a recovery code sent to an email address that was previously set up

new_hint.description: New password hint; may be empty

new_password.description: New 2-step verification password of the user; may be empty to remove the password

refundStarPayment.description: Refunds a previously done payment in Telegram Stars; for bots only

user_id.description: Identifier of the user who did the payment

registerDevice.description: Registers the currently used device for receiving push notifications. Returns a globally unique identifier of the push notification subscription @device_token Device token @other_user_ids List of user identifiers of other users currently using the application

registerUser.description: Finishes user registration. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitRegistration

disable_notification.description: Pass true to disable notification about the current user joining Telegram for other users that added them to contact list

first_name.description: The first name of the user; 1-64 characters

last_name.description: The last name of the user; 0-64 characters

removeAllFilesFromDownloads.description: Removes all files from the file download list

delete_from_cache.description: Pass true to delete the file from the TDLib file cache

only_active.description: Pass true to remove only active downloads, including paused

only_completed.description: Pass true to remove only completed downloads

removeBusinessConnectedBotFromChat.description: Removes the connected business bot from a specific chat by adding the chat to businessRecipients.excluded_chat_ids @chat_id Chat identifier

removeChatActionBar.description: Removes a chat action bar without any other action @chat_id Chat identifier

removeContacts.description: Removes users from the contact list @user_ids Identifiers of users to be deleted

removeFavoriteSticker.description: Removes a sticker from the list of favorite stickers @sticker Sticker file to delete from the list

removeFileFromDownloads.description: Removes a file from the file download list @file_id Identifier of the downloaded file @delete_from_cache Pass true to delete the file from the TDLib file cache

removeGiftCollectionGifts.description: Removes gifts from a collection. If the collection is owned by a channel chat, then requires can_post_messages administrator right in the channel chat. Returns the changed collection

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that owns the collection

received_gift_ids.description: Identifier of the gifts to remove from the collection

removeInstalledBackground.description: Removes background from the list of installed backgrounds @background_id The background identifier

removeLoginPasskey.description: Removes a passkey from the list of passkeys allowed to be used for the login by the current user @passkey_id Unique identifier of the passkey to remove

removeMessageReaction.description: Removes a reaction from a message. A chosen reaction can always be removed

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

reaction_type.description: Type of the reaction to remove. The paid reaction can't be removed

removeMessageSenderBotVerification.description: Removes the verification status of a user or a chat by an owned bot

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the owned bot, which verified the user or the chat

verified_id.description: Identifier of the user or the supergroup or channel chat, which verification is removed

removeNotification.description: Removes an active notification from notification list. Needs to be called only if the notification is removed by the current user @notification_group_id Identifier of notification group to which the notification belongs @notification_id Identifier of removed notification

removeNotificationGroup.description: Removes a group of active notifications. Needs to be called only if the notification group is removed by the current user @notification_group_id Notification group identifier @max_notification_id The maximum identifier of removed notifications

removePendingLiveStoryReactions.description: Removes all pending paid reactions in a live story group call @group_call_id Group call identifier

removePendingPaidMessageReactions.description: Removes all pending paid reactions on a message @chat_id Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs @message_id Identifier of the message

removeProfileAudio.description: Removes an audio file from the profile audio files of the current user @file_id Identifier of the audio file to be removed

removeProxy.description: Removes a proxy server. Can be called before authorization @proxy_id Proxy identifier

removeRecentHashtag.description: Removes a hashtag from the list of recently used hashtags @hashtag Hashtag to delete
