removeRecentSticker.description: Removes a sticker from the list of recently used stickers @is_attached Pass true to remove the sticker from the list of stickers recently attached to photo or video files; pass false to remove the sticker from the list of recently sent stickers @sticker Sticker file to delete

removeRecentlyFoundChat.description: Removes a chat from the list of recently found chats @chat_id Identifier of the chat to be removed

removeSavedAnimation.description: Removes an animation from the list of saved animations @animation Animation file to be removed

removeSavedNotificationSound.description: Removes a notification sound from the list of saved notification sounds @notification_sound_id Identifier of the notification sound

removeSearchedForTag.description: Removes a hashtag or a cashtag from the list of recently searched for hashtags or cashtags @tag Hashtag or cashtag to delete

removeStickerFromSet.description: Removes a sticker from the set to which it belongs. The sticker set must be owned by the current user @sticker Sticker to remove from the set

removeStoryAlbumStories.description: Removes stories from an album. If the album is owned by a supergroup or a channel chat, then

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that owns the stories

story_ids.description: Identifier of the stories to remove from the album

removeTopChat.description: Removes a chat from the list of frequently used chats. Supported only if the chat info database is enabled @category Category of frequently used chats @chat_id Chat identifier

reorderActiveUsernames.description: Changes order of active usernames of the current user @usernames The new order of active usernames. All currently active usernames must be specified

reorderBotActiveUsernames.description: Changes order of active usernames of a bot. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true @bot_user_id Identifier of the target bot @usernames The new order of active usernames. All currently active usernames must be specified

reorderBotMediaPreviews.description: Changes order of media previews in the list of media previews of a bot

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot. The bot must be owned and must have the main Web App

file_ids.description: File identifiers of the media in the new order

language_code.description: Language code of the media previews to reorder

reorderChatFolders.description: Changes the order of chat folders @chat_folder_ids Identifiers of chat folders in the new correct order @main_chat_list_position Position of the main chat list among chat folders, 0-based. Can be non-zero only for Premium users

reorderGiftCollectionGifts.description: Changes order of gifts in a collection. If the collection is owned by a channel chat, then requires can_post_messages administrator right in the channel chat. Returns the changed collection

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that owns the collection

received_gift_ids.description: Identifier of the gifts to move to the beginning of the collection. All other gifts are placed in the current order after the specified gifts

reorderGiftCollections.description: Changes order of gift collections. If the collections are owned by a channel chat, then requires can_post_messages administrator right in the channel chat

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that owns the collection

reorderInstalledStickerSets.description: Changes the order of installed sticker sets @sticker_type Type of the sticker sets to reorder @sticker_set_ids Identifiers of installed sticker sets in the new correct order

reorderQuickReplyShortcuts.description: Changes the order of quick reply shortcuts @shortcut_ids The new order of quick reply shortcuts

reorderStoryAlbumStories.description: Changes order of stories in an album. If the album is owned by a supergroup or a channel chat, then

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that owns the stories

story_ids.description: Identifier of the stories to move to the beginning of the album. All other stories are placed in the current order after the specified stories

reorderStoryAlbums.description: Changes order of story albums. If the albums are owned by a supergroup or a channel chat, then requires can_edit_stories administrator right in the chat

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that owns the stories

reorderSupergroupActiveUsernames.description: Changes order of active usernames of a supergroup or channel, requires owner privileges in the supergroup or channel

supergroup_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup or channel

usernames.description: The new order of active usernames. All currently active usernames must be specified

replaceLiveStoryRtmpUrl.description: Replaces the current RTMP URL for streaming to a live story; requires owner privileges for channel chats @chat_id Chat identifier

replacePrimaryChatInviteLink.description: Replaces current primary invite link for a chat with a new primary invite link. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right @chat_id Chat identifier

replaceStickerInSet.description: Replaces existing sticker in a set. The function is equivalent to removeStickerFromSet, then addStickerToSet, then setStickerPositionInSet

name.description: Sticker set name. The sticker set must be owned by the current user

new_sticker.description: Sticker to add to the set

old_sticker.description: Sticker to remove from the set

user_id.description: Sticker set owner; ignored for regular users

replaceVideoChatRtmpUrl.description: Replaces the current RTMP URL for streaming to the video chat of a chat; requires owner privileges in the chat @chat_id Chat identifier

reportAuthenticationCodeMissing.description: Reports that authentication code wasn't delivered via SMS; for official mobile applications only. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode @mobile_network_code Current mobile network code

reportChat.description: Reports a chat to the Telegram moderators. A chat can be reported only from the chat action bar, or if chat.can_be_reported

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

message_ids.description: Identifiers of reported messages. Use messageProperties.can_report_chat to check whether the message can be reported

option_id.description: Option identifier chosen by the user; leave empty for the initial request

text.description: Additional report details if asked by the server; 0-1024 characters; leave empty for the initial request

reportChatPhoto.description: Reports a chat photo to the Telegram moderators. A chat photo can be reported only if chat.can_be_reported

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

file_id.description: Identifier of the photo to report. Only full photos from chatPhoto can be reported

reason.description: The reason for reporting the chat photo

text.description: Additional report details; 0-1024 characters

reportChatSponsoredMessage.description: Reports a sponsored message to Telegram moderators

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the sponsored message

message_id.description: Identifier of the sponsored message

option_id.description: Option identifier chosen by the user; leave empty for the initial request

reportMessageReactions.description: Reports reactions set on a message to the Telegram moderators. Reactions on a message can be reported only if messageProperties.can_report_reactions

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

message_id.description: Message identifier

sender_id.description: Identifier of the sender, which added the reaction

reportPhoneNumberCodeMissing.description: Reports that authentication code wasn't delivered via SMS to the specified phone number; for official mobile applications only @mobile_network_code Current mobile network code

reportSponsoredChat.description: Reports a sponsored chat to Telegram moderators

option_id.description: Option identifier chosen by the user; leave empty for the initial request

sponsored_chat_unique_id.description: Unique identifier of the sponsored chat

reportStory.description: Reports a story to the Telegram moderators

option_id.description: Option identifier chosen by the user; leave empty for the initial request

story_id.description: The identifier of the story to report

story_poster_chat_id.description: The identifier of the poster of the story to report

text.description: Additional report details; 0-1024 characters; leave empty for the initial request

reportSupergroupAntiSpamFalsePositive.description: Reports a false deletion of a message by aggressive anti-spam checks; requires administrator rights in the supergroup. Can be called only for messages from chatEventMessageDeleted with can_report_anti_spam_false_positive == true

message_id.description: Identifier of the erroneously deleted message from chatEventMessageDeleted

reportSupergroupSpam.description: Reports messages in a supergroup as spam; requires administrator rights in the supergroup

message_ids.description: Identifiers of messages to report. Use messageProperties.can_report_supergroup_spam to check whether the message can be reported

reportVideoMessageAdvertisement.description: Reports a video message advertisement to Telegram moderators

option_id.description: Option identifier chosen by the user; leave empty for the initial request

requestAuthenticationPasswordRecovery.description: Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPassword

requestPasswordRecovery.description: Requests to send a 2-step verification password recovery code to an email address that was previously set up

requestQrCodeAuthentication.description: Requests QR code authentication by scanning a QR code on another logged in device. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber,

other_user_ids.description: List of user identifiers of other users currently using the application

resendAuthenticationCode.description: Resends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode, the next_code_type of the result is not null

reason.description: Reason of code resending; pass null if unknown

resendEmailAddressVerificationCode.description: Resends the code to verify an email address to be added to a user's Telegram Passport

resendLoginEmailAddressCode.description: Resends the login email address verification code

resendMessages.description: Resends messages which failed to send. Can be called only for messages for which messageSendingStateFailed.can_retry is true and after specified in messageSendingStateFailed.retry_after time passed.

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to send messages

message_ids.description: Identifiers of the messages to resend. Message identifiers must be in a strictly increasing order

paid_message_star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars the user agreed to pay to send the messages. Ignored if messageSendingStateFailed.required_paid_message_star_count == 0

quote.description: New manually chosen quote from the message to be replied; pass null if none. Ignored if more than one message is re-sent, or if messageSendingStateFailed.need_another_reply_quote == false

resendPhoneNumberCode.description: Resends the authentication code sent to a phone number. Works only if the previously received authenticationCodeInfo next_code_type was not null and the server-specified timeout has passed

reason.description: Reason of code resending; pass null if unknown

resendRecoveryEmailAddressCode.description: Resends the 2-step verification recovery email address verification code

resetAllNotificationSettings.description: Resets all chat and scope notification settings to their default values. By default, all chats are unmuted and message previews are shown

resetAuthenticationEmailAddress.description: Resets the login email address. May return an error with a message "TASK_ALREADY_EXISTS" if reset is still pending.

resetInstalledBackgrounds.description: Resets list of installed backgrounds to its default value

resetNetworkStatistics.description: Resets all network data usage statistics to zero. Can be called before authorization

resetPassword.description: Removes 2-step verification password without previous password and access to recovery email address. The password can't be reset immediately and the request needs to be repeated after the specified time

reuseStarSubscription.description: Reuses an active Telegram Star subscription to a channel chat and joins the chat again @subscription_id Identifier of the subscription

revokeChatInviteLink.description: Revokes invite link for a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires administrator privileges and can_invite_users right in the chat for own links and owner privileges for other links.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

invite_link.description: Invite link to be revoked

revokeGroupCallInviteLink.description: Revokes invite link for a group call. Requires groupCall.can_be_managed right for video chats or groupCall.is_owned otherwise @group_call_id Group call identifier

saveApplicationLogEvent.description: Saves application log event on the server. Can be called before authorization @type Event type @chat_id Optional chat identifier, associated with the event @data The log event data

savePreparedInlineMessage.description: Saves an inline message to be sent by the given user; for bots only

chat_types.description: Types of the chats to which the message can be sent

user_id.description: Identifier of the user

searchAffiliatePrograms.description: Searches affiliate programs that can be connected to the given affiliate

affiliate.description: The affiliate for which affiliate programs are searched for

limit.description: The maximum number of affiliate programs to return

offset.description: Offset of the first affiliate program to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

searchBackground.description: Searches for a background by its name @name The name of the background

searchCallMessages.description: Searches for call and group call messages. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing message_id). For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

only_missed.description: Pass true to search only for messages with missed/declined calls

searchChatAffiliateProgram.description: Searches a chat with an affiliate program. Returns the chat if found and the program is active

referrer.description: The referrer from an internalLinkTypeChatAffiliateProgram link

searchChatMembers.description: Searches for a specified query in the first name, last name and usernames of the members of a specified chat. Requires administrator rights if the chat is a channel

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

filter.description: The type of users to search for; pass null to search among all chat members

limit.description: The maximum number of users to be returned; up to 200

searchChatMessages.description: Searches for messages with given words in the chat. Returns the results in reverse chronological order, i.e. in order of decreasing message_id. Cannot be used in secret chats with a non-empty query

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which to search messages

filter.description: Additional filter for messages to search; pass null to search for all messages

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which history must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than -offset.

offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number to get the specified message and some newer messages

sender_id.description: Identifier of the sender of messages to search for; pass null to search for messages from any sender. Not supported in secret chats

topic_id.description: Pass topic identifier to search messages only in specific topic; pass null to search for messages in all topics

searchChatRecentLocationMessages.description: Returns information about the recent locations of chat members that were sent to the chat. Returns up to 1 location message per user @chat_id Chat identifier @limit The maximum number of messages to be returned

searchChats.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats. This is an offline method. Returns chats in the order seen in the main chat list

limit.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

query.description: Query to search for. If the query is empty, returns up to 50 recently found chats

searchChatsOnServer.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of already known chats via request to the server. Returns chats in the order seen in the main chat list @query Query to search for @limit The maximum number of chats to be returned

searchContacts.description: Searches for the specified query in the first names, last names and usernames of the known user contacts

limit.description: The maximum number of users to be returned

query.description: Query to search for; may be empty to return all contacts

searchEmojis.description: Searches for emojis by keywords. Supported only if the file database is enabled. Order of results is unspecified

input_language_codes.description: List of possible IETF language tags of the user's input language; may be empty if unknown

text.description: Text to search for

searchFileDownloads.description: Searches for files in the file download list or recently downloaded files from the list

limit.description: The maximum number of files to be returned

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

only_active.description: Pass true to search only for active downloads, including paused

only_completed.description: Pass true to search only for completed downloads

query.description: Query to search for; may be empty to return all downloaded files

searchGiftsForResale.description: Returns upgraded gifts that can be bought from other owners using sendResoldGift

attributes.description: Attributes used to filter received gifts. If multiple attributes of the same type are specified, then all of them are allowed.

for_crafting.description: Pass true to get only gifts suitable for crafting

gift_id.description: Identifier of the regular gift that was upgraded to a unique gift

limit.description: The maximum number of gifts to return

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request with the same order and attributes; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

order.description: Order in which the results will be sorted

searchHashtags.description: Searches for recently used hashtags by their prefix @prefix Hashtag prefix to search for @limit The maximum number of hashtags to be returned

searchInstalledStickerSets.description: Searches for installed sticker sets by looking for specified query in their title and name @sticker_type Type of the sticker sets to search for @query Query to search for @limit The maximum number of sticker sets to return

searchMessages.description: Searches for messages in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order (i.e., in order of decreasing (date, chat_id, message_id)).

chat_list.description: Chat list in which to search messages; pass null to search in all chats regardless of their chat list. Only Main and Archive chat lists are supported

chat_type_filter.description: Additional filter for type of the chat of the searched messages; pass null to search for messages in all chats

filter.description: Additional filter for messages to search; pass null to search for all messages. Filters searchMessagesFilterMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadMention, searchMessagesFilterUnreadReaction, searchMessagesFilterFailedToSend, and searchMessagesFilterPinned are unsupported in this function

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

max_date.description: If not 0, the maximum date of the messages to return

min_date.description: If not 0, the minimum date of the messages to return

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

searchOutgoingDocumentMessages.description: Searches for outgoing messages with content of the type messageDocument in all chats except secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100

query.description: Query to search for in document file name and message caption

searchPublicChat.description: Searches a public chat by its username. Currently, only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns the chat if found; otherwise, an error is returned @username Username to be resolved

searchPublicChats.description: Searches public chats by looking for specified query in their username and title. Currently, only private chats, supergroups and channels can be public. Returns a meaningful number of results.

searchPublicMessagesByTag.description: Searches for public channel posts containing the given hashtag or cashtag. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

tag.description: Hashtag or cashtag to search for

searchPublicPosts.description: Searches for public channel posts using the given query. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

star_count.description: The Telegram Star amount the user agreed to pay for the search; pass 0 for free searches

searchPublicStoriesByLocation.description: Searches for public stories by the given address location. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

limit.description: The maximum number of stories to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

searchPublicStoriesByTag.description: Searches for public stories containing the given hashtag or cashtag. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

limit.description: The maximum number of stories to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

story_poster_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that posted the stories to search for; pass 0 to search stories in all chats

tag.description: Hashtag or cashtag to search for

searchPublicStoriesByVenue.description: Searches for public stories from the given venue. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

limit.description: The maximum number of stories to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned stories is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

venue_id.description: Identifier of the venue in the provider database

searchQuote.description: Searches for a given quote in a text. Returns found quote start position in UTF-16 code units. Returns a 404 error if the quote is not found. Can be called synchronously

quote_position.description: Approximate quote position in UTF-16 code units

text.description: Text in which to search for the quote

searchRecentlyFoundChats.description: Searches for the specified query in the title and username of up to 50 recently found chats. This is an offline method

limit.description: The maximum number of chats to be returned

searchSavedMessages.description: Searches for messages tagged by the given reaction and with the given words in the Saved Messages chat; for Telegram Premium users only.

from_message_id.description: Identifier of the message starting from which messages must be fetched; use 0 to get results from the last message

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; must be positive and can't be greater than 100. If the offset is negative, then the limit must be greater than -offset.

offset.description: Specify 0 to get results from exactly the message from_message_id or a negative number to get the specified message and some newer messages

saved_messages_topic_id.description: If not 0, only messages in the specified Saved Messages topic will be considered; pass 0 to consider all messages

tag.description: Tag to search for; pass null to return all suitable messages

searchSecretMessages.description: Searches for messages in secret chats. Returns the results in reverse chronological order. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat in which to search. Specify 0 to search in all secret chats

filter.description: Additional filter for messages to search; pass null to search for all messages

limit.description: The maximum number of messages to be returned; up to 100. For optimal performance, the number of returned messages is chosen by TDLib and can be smaller than the specified limit

offset.description: Offset of the first entry to return as received from the previous request; use empty string to get the first chunk of results

query.description: Query to search for. If empty, searchChatMessages must be used instead

searchStickerSet.description: Searches for a sticker set by its name @name Name of the sticker set @ignore_cache Pass true to ignore local cache of sticker sets and always send a network request

searchStickerSets.description: Searches for sticker sets by looking for specified query in their title and name. Excludes installed sticker sets from the results

sticker_type.description: Type of the sticker sets to return

searchStickers.description: Searches for stickers from public sticker sets that correspond to any of the given emoji

emojis.description: Space-separated list of emojis to search for

input_language_codes.description: List of possible IETF language tags of the user's input language; may be empty if unknown

limit.description: The maximum number of stickers to be returned; 0-100

offset.description: The offset from which to return the stickers; must be non-negative

query.description: Query to search for; may be empty to search for emoji only

sticker_type.description: Type of the stickers to return

searchStringsByPrefix.description: Searches specified query by word prefixes in the provided strings. Returns 0-based positions of strings that matched. Can be called synchronously

limit.description: The maximum number of objects to return

return_none_for_empty_query.description: Pass true to receive no results for an empty query

strings.description: The strings to search in for the query

searchUserByPhoneNumber.description: Searches a user by their phone number. Returns a 404 error if the user can't be found

only_local.description: Pass true to get only locally available information without sending network requests

searchUserByToken.description: Searches a user by a token from the user's link @token Token to search for

searchWebApp.description: Returns information about a Web App by its short name. Returns a 404 error if the Web App is not found

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

web_app_short_name.description: Short name of the Web App

sellGift.description: Sells a gift for Telegram Stars; requires owner privileges for gifts owned by a chat

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request; for bots only

sendAuthenticationFirebaseSms.description: Sends Firebase Authentication SMS to the phone number of the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitCode and the server returned code of the type authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseAndroid or authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseIos

token.description: Play Integrity API or SafetyNet Attestation API token for the Android application, or secret from push notification for the iOS application

sendBotStartMessage.description: Invites a bot to a chat (if it is not yet a member) and sends it the /start command; requires can_invite_users member right. Bots can't be invited to a private chat other than the chat with the bot.

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot

chat_id.description: Identifier of the target chat

parameter.description: A hidden parameter sent to the bot for deep linking purposes (https://core.telegram.org/bots#deep-linking)

sendBusinessMessage.description: Sends a message on behalf of a business account; for bots only. Returns the message after it was sent

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request

chat_id.description: Target chat

disable_notification.description: Pass true to disable notification for the message

effect_id.description: Identifier of the effect to apply to the message

input_message_content.description: The content of the message to be sent

protect_content.description: Pass true if the content of the message must be protected from forwarding and saving

reply_markup.description: Markup for replying to the message; pass null if none

reply_to.description: Information about the message to be replied; pass null if none

sendBusinessMessageAlbum.description: Sends 2-10 messages grouped together into an album on behalf of a business account; for bots only. Currently, only audio, document, photo and video messages can be grouped into an album.

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request

chat_id.description: Target chat

disable_notification.description: Pass true to disable notification for the message

effect_id.description: Identifier of the effect to apply to the message

input_message_contents.description: Contents of messages to be sent. At most 10 messages can be added to an album. All messages must have the same value of show_caption_above_media

protect_content.description: Pass true if the content of the message must be protected from forwarding and saving

reply_to.description: Information about the message to be replied; pass null if none

sendCallDebugInformation.description: Sends debug information for a call to Telegram servers @call_id Call identifier @debug_information Debug information in application-specific format

sendCallLog.description: Sends log file for a call to Telegram servers @call_id Call identifier @log_file Call log file. Only inputFileLocal and inputFileGenerated are supported

comment.description: An optional user comment if the rating is less than 5

problems.description: List of the exact types of problems with the call, specified by the user

sendCallSignalingData.description: Sends call signaling data @call_id Call identifier @data The data

sendChatAction.description: Sends a notification about user activity in a chat

action.description: The action description; pass null to cancel the currently active action

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request; for bots only

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

topic_id.description: Identifier of the topic in which the action is performed; pass null if none

sendCustomRequest.description: Sends a custom request; for bots only @method The method name @parameters JSON-serialized method parameters

sendEmailAddressVerificationCode.description: Sends a code to verify an email address to be added to a user's Telegram Passport @email_address Email address

sendGift.description: Sends a gift to another user or channel chat. May return an error with a message "STARGIFT_USAGE_LIMITED" if the gift was sold out

gift_id.description: Identifier of the gift to send

is_private.description: Pass true to show gift text and sender only to the gift receiver; otherwise, everyone will be able to see them

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that will receive the gift; limited gifts can't be sent to channel chats

pay_for_upgrade.description: Pass true to additionally pay for the gift upgrade and allow the receiver to upgrade it for free

text.description: Text to show along with the gift; 0-getOption("gift_text_length_max") characters. Only Bold, Italic, Underline, Strikethrough, Spoiler, and CustomEmoji entities are allowed.

sendGiftPurchaseOffer.description: Sends an offer to purchase an upgraded gift

duration.description: Duration of the offer, in seconds; must be one of 21600, 43200, 86400, 129600, 172800, or 259200. Can also be 120 if Telegram test environment is used

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that currently owns the gift and will receive the offer

paid_message_star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars the user agreed to pay additionally for sending of the offer message to the current gift owner; pass userFullInfo.outgoing_paid_message_star_count for users and 0 otherwise

price.description: The price that the user agreed to pay for the gift

sendGroupCallMessage.description: Sends a message to other participants of a group call. Requires groupCall.can_send_messages right

paid_message_star_count.description: The number of Telegram Stars the user agreed to pay to send the message; for live stories only; 0-getOption("paid_group_call_message_star_count_max").

text.description: Text of the message to send; 1-getOption("group_call_message_text_length_max") characters for non-live-stories; see updateGroupCallMessageLevels for live story restrictions,

sendInlineQueryResultMessage.description: Sends the result of an inline query as a message. Returns the sent message. Always clears a chat draft message

chat_id.description: Target chat

hide_via_bot.description: Pass true to hide the bot, via which the message is sent. Can be used only for bots getOption("animation_search_bot_username"), getOption("photo_search_bot_username"), and getOption("venue_search_bot_username")

options.description: Options to be used to send the message; pass null to use default options

reply_to.description: Information about the message or story to be replied; pass null if none

result_id.description: Identifier of the inline query result

topic_id.description: Topic in which the message will be sent; pass null if none

sendMessage.description: Sends a message. Returns the sent message

chat_id.description: Target chat

input_message_content.description: The content of the message to be sent

options.description: Options to be used to send the message; pass null to use default options

reply_markup.description: Markup for replying to the message; pass null if none; for bots only

reply_to.description: Information about the message or story to be replied; pass null if none

topic_id.description: Topic in which the message will be sent; pass null if none

sendMessageAlbum.description: Sends 2-10 messages grouped together into an album. Currently, only audio, document, photo and video messages can be grouped into an album.

chat_id.description: Target chat

input_message_contents.description: Contents of messages to be sent. At most 10 messages can be added to an album. All messages must have the same value of show_caption_above_media

options.description: Options to be used to send the messages; pass null to use default options

reply_to.description: Information about the message or story to be replied; pass null if none

topic_id.description: Topic in which the messages will be sent; pass null if none

sendPassportAuthorizationForm.description: Sends a Telegram Passport authorization form, effectively sharing data with the service. This method must be called after getPassportAuthorizationFormAvailableElements if some previously available elements are going to be reused

types.description: Types of Telegram Passport elements chosen by user to complete the authorization form

sendPaymentForm.description: Sends a filled-out payment form to the bot for final verification

credentials.description: The credentials chosen by user for payment; pass null for a payment in Telegram Stars

order_info_id.description: Identifier returned by validateOrderInfo, or an empty string

payment_form_id.description: Payment form identifier returned by getPaymentForm

shipping_option_id.description: Identifier of a chosen shipping option, if applicable

tip_amount.description: Chosen by the user amount of tip in the smallest units of the currency

sendPhoneNumberCode.description: Sends a code to the specified phone number. Aborts previous phone number verification if there was one. On success, returns information about the sent code

phone_number.description: The phone number, in international format

settings.description: Settings for the authentication of the user's phone number; pass null to use default settings

type.description: Type of the request for which the code is sent

sendPhoneNumberFirebaseSms.description: Sends Firebase Authentication SMS to the specified phone number. Works only when received a code of the type authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseAndroid or authenticationCodeTypeFirebaseIos

token.description: Play Integrity API or SafetyNet Attestation API token for the Android application, or secret from push notification for the iOS application

sendQuickReplyShortcutMessages.description: Sends messages from a quick reply shortcut. Requires Telegram Business subscription. Can't be used to send paid messages

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which to send messages. The chat must be a private chat with a regular user

sending_id.description: Non-persistent identifier, which will be returned back in messageSendingStatePending object and can be used to match sent messages and corresponding updateNewMessage updates

shortcut_id.description: Unique identifier of the quick reply shortcut

sendResoldGift.description: Sends an upgraded gift that is available for resale to another user or channel chat; gifts already owned by the current user

gift_name.description: Name of the upgraded gift to send

owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that will receive the gift

price.description: The price that the user agreed to pay for the gift

sendTextMessageDraft.description: Sends a draft for a being generated text message; for bots only

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

forum_topic_id.description: The forum topic identifier in which the message will be sent; pass 0 if none

text.description: Draft text of the message

sendWebAppCustomRequest.description: Sends a custom request from a Web App

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the bot

sendWebAppData.description: Sends data received from a keyboardButtonTypeWebApp Web App to a bot

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

button_text.description: Text of the keyboardButtonTypeWebApp button, which opened the Web App

setAccentColor.description: Changes accent color and background custom emoji for the current user; for Telegram Premium users only

accent_color_id.description: Identifier of the accent color to use

background_custom_emoji_id.description: Identifier of a custom emoji to be shown on the reply header and link preview background; 0 if none

setAccountTtl.description: Changes the period of inactivity after which the account of the current user will automatically be deleted @ttl New account TTL

setAlarm.description: Succeeds after a specified amount of time has passed. Can be called before initialization @seconds Number of seconds before the function returns

setApplicationVerificationToken.description: Informs TDLib that application or reCAPTCHA verification has been completed. Can be called before authorization

token.description: Play Integrity API token for the Android application, or secret from push notification for the iOS application for application verification, or reCAPTCHA token for reCAPTCHA verifications;

verification_id.description: Unique identifier for the verification process as received from updateApplicationVerificationRequired or updateApplicationRecaptchaVerificationRequired

setArchiveChatListSettings.description: Changes settings for automatic moving of chats to and from the Archive chat lists @settings New settings

setAuthenticationEmailAddress.description: Sets the email address of the user and sends an authentication code to the email address. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitEmailAddress @email_address The email address of the user

setAuthenticationPhoneNumber.description: Sets the phone number of the user and sends an authentication code to the user. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPhoneNumber,

phone_number.description: The phone number of the user, in international format

settings.description: Settings for the authentication of the user's phone number; pass null to use default settings

setAuthenticationPremiumPurchaseTransact.description: Informs server about an in-store purchase of Telegram Premium before authorization. Works only when the current authorization state is authorizationStateWaitPremiumPurchase

amount.description: Paid amount, in the smallest units of the currency

currency.description: ISO 4217 currency code of the payment currency

is_restore.description: Pass true if this is a restore of a Telegram Premium purchase; only for App Store

setAutoDownloadSettings.description: Sets auto-download settings @settings New user auto-download settings @type Type of the network for which the new settings are relevant

setAutosaveSettings.description: Sets autosave settings for the given scope. The method is guaranteed to work only after at least one call to getAutosaveSettings @scope Autosave settings scope @settings New autosave settings for the scope; pass null to set autosave settings to default

setBio.description: Changes the bio of the current user @bio The new value of the user bio; 0-getOption("bio_length_max") characters without line feeds

setBirthdate.description: Changes the birthdate of the current user @birthdate The new value of the current user's birthdate; pass null to remove the birthdate

setBotInfoDescription.description: Sets the text shown in the chat with a bot if the chat is empty. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

description.description: New bot's description on the specified language

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code. If empty, the description will be shown to all users for whose languages there is no dedicated description

setBotInfoShortDescription.description: Sets the text shown on a bot's profile page and sent together with the link when users share the bot. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code. If empty, the short description will be shown to all users for whose languages there is no dedicated description

short_description.description: New bot's short description on the specified language

setBotName.description: Sets the name of a bot. Can be called only if userTypeBot.can_be_edited == true

bot_user_id.description: Identifier of the target bot

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code. If empty, the name will be shown to all users for whose languages there is no dedicated name

name.description: New bot's name on the specified language; 0-64 characters; must be non-empty if language code is empty

setBotProfilePhoto.description: Changes a profile photo for a bot @bot_user_id Identifier of the target bot @photo Profile photo to set; pass null to delete the chat photo

setBotUpdatesStatus.description: Informs the server about the number of pending bot updates if they haven't been processed for a long time; for bots only @pending_update_count The number of pending updates @error_message The last error message

setBusinessAccountBio.description: Changes the bio of a business account; for bots only

bio.description: The new value of the bio; 0-getOption("bio_length_max") characters without line feeds

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection

setBusinessAccountGiftSettings.description: Changes settings for gift receiving of a business account; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection

setBusinessAccountName.description: Changes the first and last name of a business account; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection

first_name.description: The new value of the first name for the business account; 1-64 characters

last_name.description: The new value of the optional last name for the business account; 0-64 characters

setBusinessAccountProfilePhoto.description: Changes a profile photo of a business account; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection

is_public.description: Pass true to set the public photo, which will be visible even if the main photo is hidden by privacy settings

photo.description: Profile photo to set; pass null to remove the photo

setBusinessAccountUsername.description: Changes the editable username of a business account; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection

username.description: The new value of the username

setBusinessAwayMessageSettings.description: Changes the business away message settings of the current user. Requires Telegram Business subscription @away_message_settings The new settings for the away message of the business; pass null to disable the away message

setBusinessConnectedBot.description: Adds or changes business bot that is connected to the current user account @bot Connection settings for the bot

setBusinessGreetingMessageSettings.description: Changes the business greeting message settings of the current user. Requires Telegram Business subscription @greeting_message_settings The new settings for the greeting message of the business; pass null to disable the greeting message

setBusinessLocation.description: Changes the business location of the current user. Requires Telegram Business subscription @location The new location of the business; pass null to remove the location

setBusinessMessageIsPinned.description: Pins or unpins a message sent on behalf of a business account; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which the message was sent

chat_id.description: The chat the message belongs to

is_pinned.description: Pass true to pin the message, pass false to unpin it

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

setBusinessOpeningHours.description: Changes the business opening hours of the current user. Requires Telegram Business subscription

opening_hours.description: The new opening hours of the business; pass null to remove the opening hours; up to 28 time intervals can be specified

setBusinessStartPage.description: Changes the business start page of the current user. Requires Telegram Business subscription @start_page The new start page of the business; pass null to remove custom start page

setChatAccentColor.description: Changes accent color and background custom emoji of a channel chat. Requires can_change_info administrator right

accent_color_id.description: Identifier of the accent color to use. The chat must have at least accentColor.min_channel_chat_boost_level boost level to pass the corresponding color

background_custom_emoji_id.description: Identifier of a custom emoji to be shown on the reply header and link preview background; 0 if none. Use chatBoostLevelFeatures.can_set_background_custom_emoji to check whether a custom emoji can be set

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

setChatActiveStoriesList.description: Changes story list in which stories from the chat are shown @chat_id Identifier of the chat that posted stories @story_list New list for active stories posted by the chat

setChatAffiliateProgram.description: Changes affiliate program for a bot

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat with an owned bot for which affiliate program is changed

parameters.description: Parameters of the affiliate program; pass null to close the currently active program. If there is an active program, then commission and program duration can only be increased.

setChatAvailableReactions.description: Changes reactions, available in a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires can_change_info member right

available_reactions.description: Reactions available in the chat. All explicitly specified emoji reactions must be active. In channel chats up to the chat's boost level custom emoji reactions can be explicitly specified

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

setChatBackground.description: Sets the background in a specific chat. Supported only in private and secret chats with non-deleted users, and in chats with sufficient boost level and can_change_info administrator right

background.description: The input background to use; pass null to create a new filled or chat theme background

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

dark_theme_dimming.description: Dimming of the background in dark themes, as a percentage; 0-100. Applied only to Wallpaper and Fill types of background

only_for_self.description: Pass true to set background only for self; pass false to set background for all chat users. Always false for backgrounds set in boosted chats. Background can be set for both users only by Telegram Premium users and if set background isn't of the type inputBackgroundPrevious

type.description: Background type; pass null to use default background type for the chosen background; backgroundTypeChatTheme isn't supported for private and secret chats.

setChatClientData.description: Changes application-specific data associated with a chat @chat_id Chat identifier @client_data New value of client_data

setChatDescription.description: Changes information about a chat. Available for basic groups, supergroups, and channels. Requires can_change_info member right @chat_id Identifier of the chat @param_description New chat description; 0-255 characters

setChatDirectMessagesGroup.description: Changes direct messages group settings for a channel chat; requires owner privileges in the chat

chat_id.description: Identifier of the channel chat

is_enabled.description: Pass true if the direct messages group is enabled for the channel chat; pass false otherwise

paid_message_star_count.description: The new number of Telegram Stars that must be paid for each message that is sent to the direct messages chat unless the sender is an administrator of the channel chat; 0-getOption("paid_message_star_count_max").

setChatDiscussionGroup.description: Changes the discussion group of a channel chat; requires can_change_info administrator right in the channel if it is specified

chat_id.description: Identifier of the channel chat. Pass 0 to remove a link from the supergroup passed in the second argument to a linked channel chat (requires can_pin_messages member right in the supergroup)

discussion_chat_id.description: Identifier of a new channel's discussion group. Use 0 to remove the discussion group. Use the method getSuitableDiscussionChats to find all suitable groups.

setChatDraftMessage.description: Changes the draft message in a chat or a topic

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

draft_message.description: New draft message; pass null to remove the draft. All files in draft message content must be of the type inputFileLocal. Media thumbnails and captions are ignored

topic_id.description: Topic in which the draft will be changed; pass null to change the draft for the chat itself

setChatEmojiStatus.description: Changes the emoji status of a chat. Use chatBoostLevelFeatures.can_set_emoji_status to check whether an emoji status can be set. Requires can_change_info administrator right

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

emoji_status.description: New emoji status; pass null to remove emoji status

setChatLocation.description: Changes the location of a chat. Available only for some location-based supergroups, use supergroupFullInfo.can_set_location to check whether the method is allowed to use @chat_id Chat identifier @location New location for the chat; must be valid and not null

setChatMemberStatus.description: Changes the status of a chat member; requires can_invite_users member right to add a chat member, can_promote_members administrator right to change administrator rights of the member,

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

member_id.description: Member identifier. Chats can be only banned and unbanned in supergroups and channels

status.description: The new status of the member in the chat

setChatMessageAutoDeleteTime.description: Changes the message auto-delete or self-destruct (for secret chats) time in a chat. Requires change_info administrator right in basic groups, supergroups and channels.

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

message_auto_delete_time.description: New time value, in seconds; unless the chat is secret, it must be from 0 up to 365 * 86400 and be divisible by 86400. If 0, then messages aren't deleted automatically

setChatMessageSender.description: Selects a message sender to send messages in a chat @chat_id Chat identifier @message_sender_id New message sender for the chat

setChatNotificationSettings.description: Changes the notification settings of a chat. Notification settings of a chat with the current user (Saved Messages) can't be changed

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

notification_settings.description: New notification settings for the chat. If the chat is muted for more than 366 days, it is considered to be muted forever

setChatPaidMessageStarCount.description: Changes the Telegram Star amount that must be paid to send a message to a supergroup chat; requires can_restrict_members administrator right and supergroupFullInfo.can_enable_paid_messages

chat_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup chat

paid_message_star_count.description: The new number of Telegram Stars that must be paid for each message that is sent to the supergroup chat unless the sender is an administrator of the chat; 0-getOption("paid_message_star_count_max").

setChatPermissions.description: Changes the chat members permissions. Supported only for basic groups and supergroups. Requires can_restrict_members administrator right

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

permissions.description: New non-administrator members permissions in the chat

setChatPhoto.description: Changes the photo of a chat. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires can_change_info member right

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

photo.description: New chat photo; pass null to delete the chat photo

setChatPinnedStories.description: Changes the list of pinned stories on a chat page; requires can_edit_stories administrator right in the chat

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that posted the stories

story_ids.description: New list of pinned stories. All stories must be posted to the chat page first. There can be up to getOption("pinned_story_count_max") pinned stories on a chat page

setChatProfileAccentColor.description: Changes accent color and background custom emoji for profile of a supergroup or channel chat. Requires can_change_info administrator right

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

profile_accent_color_id.description: Identifier of the accent color to use for profile; pass -1 if none. The chat must have at least profileAccentColor.min_supergroup_chat_boost_level for supergroups

profile_background_custom_emoji_id.description: Identifier of a custom emoji to be shown on the chat's profile photo background; 0 if none. Use chatBoostLevelFeatures.can_set_profile_background_custom_emoji to check whether a custom emoji can be set

setChatSlowModeDelay.description: Changes the slow mode delay of a chat. Available only for supergroups; requires can_restrict_members administrator right @chat_id Chat identifier @slow_mode_delay New slow mode delay for the chat, in seconds; must be one of 0, 5, 10, 30, 60, 300, 900, 3600

setChatTheme.description: Changes the chat theme. Supported only in private and secret chats @chat_id Chat identifier @theme New chat theme; pass null to return the default theme

setChatTitle.description: Changes the chat title. Supported only for basic groups, supergroups and channels. Requires can_change_info member right

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

title.description: New title of the chat; 1-128 characters

setCloseFriends.description: Changes the list of close friends of the current user @user_ids User identifiers of close friends; the users must be contacts of the current user

setCommands.description: Sets the list of commands supported by the bot for the given user scope and language; for bots only

language_code.description: A two-letter ISO 639-1 language code. If empty, the commands will be applied to all users from the given scope, for which language there are no dedicated commands

scope.description: The scope to which the commands are relevant; pass null to change commands in the default bot command scope

setCustomEmojiStickerSetThumbnail.description: Sets a custom emoji sticker set thumbnail

custom_emoji_id.description: Identifier of the custom emoji from the sticker set, which will be set as sticker set thumbnail; pass 0 to remove the sticker set thumbnail

name.description: Sticker set name. The sticker set must be owned by the current user

setCustomLanguagePack.description: Adds or changes a custom local language pack to the current localization target

info.description: Information about the language pack. Language pack identifier must start with 'X', consist only of English letters, digits and hyphens, and must not exceed 64 characters. Can be called before authorization

strings.description: Strings of the new language pack

setCustomLanguagePackString.description: Adds, edits or deletes a string in a custom local language pack. Can be called before authorization @language_pack_id Identifier of a previously added custom local language pack in the current localization target @new_string New language pack string

setDatabaseEncryptionKey.description: Changes the database encryption key. Usually the encryption key is never changed and is stored in some OS keychain @new_encryption_key New encryption key

setDefaultBackground.description: Sets default background for chats; adds the background to the list of installed backgrounds

background.description: The input background to use; pass null to create a new filled background

for_dark_theme.description: Pass true if the background is set for a dark theme

type.description: Background type; pass null to use the default type of the remote background; backgroundTypeChatTheme isn't supported

setDefaultChannelAdministratorRights.description: Sets default administrator rights for adding the bot to channel chats; for bots only @default_channel_administrator_rights Default administrator rights for adding the bot to channels; pass null to remove default rights

setDefaultGroupAdministratorRights.description: Sets default administrator rights for adding the bot to basic group and supergroup chats; for bots only @default_group_administrator_rights Default administrator rights for adding the bot to basic group and supergroup chats; pass null to remove default rights

setDefaultMessageAutoDeleteTime.description: Changes the default message auto-delete time for new chats @message_auto_delete_time New default message auto-delete time; must be from 0 up to 365 * 86400 and be divisible by 86400. If 0, then messages aren't deleted automatically

setDefaultReactionType.description: Changes type of default reaction for the current user @reaction_type New type of the default reaction. The paid reaction can't be set as default

setDirectMessagesChatTopicIsMarkedAsUnre.description: Changes the marked as unread state of the topic in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user

chat_id.description: Chat identifier of the channel direct messages chat

topic_id.description: Topic identifier

setEmojiStatus.description: Changes the emoji status of the current user; for Telegram Premium users only @emoji_status New emoji status; pass null to switch to the default badge

setFileGenerationProgress.description: Informs TDLib on a file generation progress

expected_size.description: Expected size of the generated file, in bytes; 0 if unknown

generation_id.description: The identifier of the generation process

local_prefix_size.description: The number of bytes already generated

setForumTopicNotificationSettings.description: Changes the notification settings of a forum topic in a forum supergroup chat or a chat with a bot with topics

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

notification_settings.description: New notification settings for the forum topic. If the topic is muted for more than 366 days, it is considered to be muted forever

setGameScore.description: Updates the game score of the specified user in the game; for bots only

chat_id.description: The chat to which the message with the game belongs

edit_message.description: Pass true to edit the game message to include the current scoreboard

force.description: Pass true to update the score even if it decreases. If the score is 0, the user will be deleted from the high score table

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

user_id.description: User identifier

There can be up to getOption("pinned_chat_count_max")/getOption("pinned_archived_chat_count_max") pinned non-secret chats and the same number of secret chats in the main/archive chat list. The limit can be increased with Telegram Premium

is_pinned.description: Pass true to pin the topic; pass false to unpin it

saved_messages_topic_id.description: Identifier of Saved Messages topic to pin or unpin

toggleSessionCanAcceptCalls.description: Toggles whether a session can accept incoming calls @session_id Session identifier @can_accept_calls Pass true to allow accepting incoming calls by the session; pass false otherwise

toggleSessionCanAcceptSecretChats.description: Toggles whether a session can accept incoming secret chats @session_id Session identifier @can_accept_secret_chats Pass true to allow accepting secret chats by the session; pass false otherwise

toggleStoryIsPostedToChatPage.description: Toggles whether a story is accessible after expiration. Can be called only if story.can_toggle_is_posted_to_chat_page == true

is_posted_to_chat_page.description: Pass true to make the story accessible after expiration; pass false to make it private

story_poster_chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat that posted the story

toggleSupergroupCanHaveSponsoredMessages.description: Toggles whether sponsored messages are shown in the channel chat; requires owner privileges in the channel. The chat must have at least chatBoostFeatures.min_sponsored_message_disable_boost_level boost level to disable sponsored messages

toggleSupergroupHasAggressiveAntiSpamEna.description: Toggles whether aggressive anti-spam checks are enabled in the supergroup. Can be called only if supergroupFullInfo.can_toggle_aggressive_anti_spam == true

supergroup_id.description: The identifier of the supergroup, which isn't a broadcast group

toggleSupergroupHasAutomaticTranslation.description: Toggles whether messages are automatically translated in the channel chat; requires can_change_info administrator right in the channel.

toggleSupergroupHasHiddenMembers.description: Toggles whether non-administrators can receive only administrators and bots using getSupergroupMembers or searchChatMembers. Can be called only if supergroupFullInfo.can_hide_members == true

toggleSupergroupIsAllHistoryAvailable.description: Toggles whether the message history of a supergroup is available to new members; requires can_change_info member right @supergroup_id The identifier of the supergroup @is_all_history_available The new value of is_all_history_available

toggleSupergroupIsBroadcastGroup.description: Upgrades supergroup to a broadcast group; requires owner privileges in the supergroup @supergroup_id Identifier of the supergroup

toggleSupergroupIsForum.description: Toggles whether the supergroup is a forum; requires owner privileges in the supergroup. Discussion supergroups can't be converted to forums

has_forum_tabs.description: New value of has_forum_tabs; ignored if is_forum is false

toggleSupergroupJoinByRequest.description: Toggles whether all users directly joining the supergroup need to be approved by supergroup administrators; requires can_restrict_members administrator right

supergroup_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup that isn't a broadcast group and isn't a channel direct message group

toggleSupergroupJoinToSendMessages.description: Toggles whether joining is mandatory to send messages to a discussion supergroup; requires can_restrict_members administrator right

supergroup_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup that isn't a broadcast group

toggleSupergroupSignMessages.description: Toggles whether sender signature or link to the account is added to sent messages in a channel; requires can_change_info member right

toggleSupergroupUsernameIsActive.description: Changes active state for a username of a supergroup or channel, requires owner privileges in the supergroup or channel. The editable username can't be disabled.

is_active.description: Pass true to activate the username; pass false to disable it

supergroup_id.description: Identifier of the supergroup or channel

toggleUsernameIsActive.description: Changes active state for a username of the current user. The editable username can't be disabled. May return an error with a message "USERNAMES_ACTIVE_TOO_MUCH" if the maximum number of active usernames has been reached

is_active.description: Pass true to activate the username; pass false to disable it

toggleVideoChatEnabledStartNotification.description: Toggles whether the current user will receive a notification when the video chat starts; for scheduled video chats only

enabled_start_notification.description: New value of the enabled_start_notification setting

toggleVideoChatMuteNewParticipants.description: Toggles whether new participants of a video chat can be unmuted only by administrators of the video chat. Requires groupCall.can_toggle_mute_new_participants right

mute_new_participants.description: New value of the mute_new_participants setting

transferBusinessAccountStars.description: Transfers Telegram Stars from the business account to the business bot; for bots only

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection

star_count.description: Number of Telegram Stars to transfer

transferChatOwnership.description: Changes the owner of a chat; requires owner privileges in the chat. Use the method canTransferOwnership to check whether the ownership can be transferred from the current session. Available only for supergroups and channel chats

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

password.description: The 2-step verification password of the current user

user_id.description: Identifier of the user to which transfer the ownership. The ownership can't be transferred to a bot or to a deleted user

transferGift.description: Sends an upgraded gift to another user or channel chat

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request; for bots only

new_owner_id.description: Identifier of the user or the channel chat that will receive the gift

star_count.description: The Telegram Star amount required to pay for the transfer

translateMessageText.description: Extracts text or caption of the given message and translates it to the given language. If the current user is a Telegram Premium user, then text formatting is preserved

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat to which the message belongs

message_id.description: Identifier of the message

to_language_code.description: Language code of the language to which the message is translated. See translateText.to_language_code for the list of supported values

translateText.description: Translates a text to the given language. If the current user is a Telegram Premium user, then text formatting is preserved

text.description: Text to translate

to_language_code.description: Language code of the language to which the message is translated. Must be one of

unpinAllChatMessages.description: Removes all pinned messages from a chat; requires can_pin_messages member right if the chat is a basic group or supergroup, or can_edit_messages administrator right if the chat is a channel @chat_id Identifier of the chat

unpinAllDirectMessagesChatTopicMessages.description: Removes all pinned messages from the topic in a channel direct messages chat administered by the current user

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

topic_id.description: Topic identifier

unpinAllForumTopicMessages.description: Removes all pinned messages from a topic in a forum supergroup chat or a chat with a bot with topics; requires can_pin_messages member right in the supergroup

chat_id.description: Identifier of the chat

forum_topic_id.description: Forum topic identifier in which messages will be unpinned

unpinChatMessage.description: Removes a pinned message from a chat; requires can_pin_messages member right if the chat is a basic group or supergroup, or can_edit_messages administrator right if the chat is a channel @chat_id Identifier of the chat @message_id Identifier of the removed pinned message

upgradeBasicGroupChatToSupergroupChat.description: Creates a new supergroup from an existing basic group and sends a corresponding messageChatUpgradeTo and messageChatUpgradeFrom; requires owner privileges. Deactivates the original basic group @chat_id Identifier of the chat to upgrade

business_connection_id.description: Unique identifier of business connection on behalf of which to send the request; for bots only

keep_original_details.description: Pass true to keep the original gift text, sender and receiver in the upgraded gift

star_count.description: The Telegram Star amount required to pay for the upgrade. It the gift has prepaid_upgrade_star_count > 0, then pass 0, otherwise, pass gift.upgrade_star_count

uploadStickerFile.description: Uploads a file with a sticker; returns the uploaded file

sticker.description: File file to upload; must fit in a 512x512 square. For WEBP stickers the file must be in WEBP or PNG format, which will be converted to WEBP server-side.

user_id.description: Sticker file owner; ignored for regular users

validateOrderInfo.description: Validates the order information provided by a user and returns the available shipping options for a flexible invoice

allow_save.description: Pass true to save the order information

order_info.description: The order information, provided by the user; pass null if empty

viewMessages.description: Informs TDLib that messages are being viewed by the user. Sponsored messages must be marked as viewed only when the entire text of the message is shown on the screen (excluding the button).

chat_id.description: Chat identifier

force_read.description: Pass true to mark as read the specified messages even if the chat is closed

message_ids.description: The identifiers of the messages being viewed

source.description: Source of the message view; pass null to guess the source based on chat open state

viewPremiumFeature.description: Informs TDLib that the user viewed detailed information about a Premium feature on the Premium features screen @feature The viewed premium feature

viewSponsoredChat.description: Informs TDLib that the user fully viewed a sponsored chat @sponsored_chat_unique_id Unique identifier of the sponsored chat

viewTrendingStickerSets.description: Informs the server that some trending sticker sets have been viewed by the user @sticker_set_ids Identifiers of viewed trending sticker sets

viewVideoMessageAdvertisement.description: Informs TDLib that the user viewed a video message advertisement @advertisement_unique_id Unique identifier of the advertisement

writeGeneratedFilePart.description: Writes a part of a generated file. This method is intended to be used only if the application has no direct access to TDLib's file system, because it is usually slower than a direct write to the destination file

generation_id.description: The identifier of the generation process

offset.description: The offset from which to write the data to the file
